  <graph edgedefault="directed">
    <node id="OBL-0001">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Securitisation exposures are addressed in the securitisation standard.1 Credit equivalent amounts
of OTC derivatives, exchange traded derivatives and long-settlement transactions that expose a bank to
counterparty credit risk2 are to be calculated under the counterparty credit risk standards.3 Equity
investments in funds and exposures to central counterparties must be treated according to their own
specific frameworks.4
1 The securitisation standard is available at www.bis.org/bcbs/publ/d374.pdf.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">calculate credit equivalent amounts of OTC derivatives, exchange traded derivatives and long-settlement transactions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:bank">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">bank</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0001">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">that expose a bank to counterparty credit risk</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0002">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Consistent with the Committee’s guidance on the assessment of credit risk5 and paragraphs 733
to 735 of the Basel II framework (June 2006), banks must perform due diligence to ensure that they have
an adequate understanding, at origination and thereafter on a regular basis (at least annually), of the risk
profile and characteristics of their counterparties.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">perform due diligence to ensure that they have an adequate understanding of the risk profile and characteristics of their counterparties</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:banks">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">banks</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0002">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">at origination and thereafter on a regular basis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0002">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">at least annually</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0003">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must take reasonable and adequate steps to assess the
operating and financial performance levels and trends through internal credit analysis and/or other
analytics outsourced to a third party, as appropriate for each counterparty.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">take reasonable and adequate steps to assess the operating and financial performance levels and trends</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Banks">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Banks</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0003">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">as appropriate for each counterparty</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0004">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must be able to access
information about their counterparties on a regular basis to complete due diligence analyses.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">be able to access information about their counterparties</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0004">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to complete due diligence analyses</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0004">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">on a regular basis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0005">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must be able to demonstrate to
their supervisors that their due diligence analyses are appropriate.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">demonstrate to their supervisors that their due diligence analyses are appropriate</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0006">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">As part of their supervisory review,
supervisors should ensure that banks have appropriately performed their due diligence analyses, and
should take supervisory measures where these have not been done.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure that banks have appropriately performed their due diligence analyses and take supervisory measures where these have not been done</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:supervisors">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">supervisors</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0006">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">as part of their supervisory review</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0007">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">To qualify, an ECA must publish its risk
scores and subscribe to the OECD-agreed methodology.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">publish its risk scores and subscribe to the OECD-agreed methodology</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:an ECA">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">an ECA</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0007">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to qualify</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0008">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The eligibility criteria for MDBs risk-weighted at 0% are:
(i) very high-quality long-term issuer ratings, ie a majority of an MDB’s external ratings must be
AAA;12
10 The following examples outline how PSEs might be categorised when focusing on one specific feature, namely revenue-raising
powers.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">must have very high-quality long-term issuer ratings</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:MDBs">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">MDBs</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0008">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to be risk-weighted at 0%</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0008">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">a majority of an MDB’s external ratings must be AAA</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0009">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">12 MDBs that request to be added to the list of MDBs eligible for a 0% risk weight must comply with the AAA rating criterion at
the time of the application.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">comply with the AAA rating criterion</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:12 MDBs">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">12 MDBs</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0009">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">at the time of the application to be added to the list of MDBs eligible for a 0% risk weight</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0009">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">at the time of the application</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0010">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Such ratings must not incorporate assumptions of implicit
government support, unless the rating refers to a public bank owned by its government.16 Banks
incorporated in jurisdictions that allow the use of external ratings for regulatory purposes must only apply
SCRA for their unrated bank exposures, in accordance with paragraph 21.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">only apply SCRA for their unrated bank exposures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Banks incorporated in jurisdictions that allow the use of external ratings for regulatory purposes">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Banks incorporated in jurisdictions that allow the use of external ratings for regulatory purposes</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0010">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in accordance with paragraph 21</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0010">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">ratings may incorporate assumptions of implicit government support if the rating refers to a public bank owned by its government</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0011">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must perform due diligence to ensure that the external ratings appropriately and
conservatively reflect the creditworthiness of the bank counterparties.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">perform due diligence to ensure that the external ratings appropriately and conservatively reflect the creditworthiness of the bank counterparties</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0012">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A+ to A– etc), the bank must assign a risk weight at least one bucket higher than the “base” risk weight
determined by the external rating.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">assign a risk weight at least one bucket higher than the “base” risk weight determined by the external rating</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the bank">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the bank</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0012">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if the rating is A+ to A– etc</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0013">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Due diligence analysis must never result in the application of a lower
risk weight than that determined by the external rating.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">must not result in the application of a lower risk weight than that determined by the external rating</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Due diligence analysis">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Due diligence analysis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0014">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A counterparty bank classified into Grade A must meet or exceed the published minimum
regulatory requirements and buffers established by its national supervisor as implemented in the
jurisdiction where it is incorporated, except for bank-specific minimum regulatory requirements or buffers
that may be imposed through supervisory actions (eg via Pillar 2) and not made public.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">must meet or exceed the published minimum regulatory requirements and buffers established by its national supervisor as implemented in the jurisdiction where it is incorporated</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:A counterparty bank classified into Grade A">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">A counterparty bank classified into Grade A</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0014">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">as implemented in the jurisdiction where it is incorporated</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0014">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">except for bank-specific minimum regulatory requirements or buffers that may be imposed through supervisory actions (eg via Pillar 2) and not made public</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0015">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">If such minimum
regulatory requirements and buffers (other than bank-specific minimum requirements or buffers) are not
publicly disclosed or otherwise made available by the counterparty bank then the counterparty bank must
be assessed as Grade B or lower.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">be assessed as Grade B or lower</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:counterparty bank">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">counterparty bank</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0015">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if minimum regulatory requirements and buffers (other than bank-specific minimum requirements or buffers) are not publicly disclosed or otherwise made available by the counterparty bank</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0015">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">bank-specific minimum requirements or buffers</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0016">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">If as part of its due diligence, a bank assesses that a counterparty bank does not meet the
definition of Grade A in paragraphs 22 and 23, exposures to the counterparty bank must be classified as
Grade B or Grade C.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">classify exposures to the counterparty bank as Grade B or Grade C</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:a bank">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">a bank</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0016">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if the bank assesses that a counterparty bank does not meet the definition of Grade A in paragraphs 22 and 23</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0017">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A counterparty bank classified into Grade B must meet or exceed the published minimum
regulatory requirements (excluding buffers) established by its national supervisor as implemented in the
18 Under the Standardised Credit Risk Assessment Approach, exposures to banks without an external credit rating may receive a
risk weight of 30%, provided that the counterparty bank has a CET1 ratio which meets or exceeds 14% and a Tier 1 leverage
ratio which meets or exceeds 5%.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">receive a risk weight of 30% under the Standardised Credit Risk Assessment Approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:counterparty bank without an external credit rating">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">counterparty bank without an external credit rating</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0017">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">exposures to banks without an external credit rating</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0017">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">CET1 ratio which meets or exceeds 14% and a Tier 1 leverage ratio which meets or exceeds 5%</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0018">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The counterparty bank must also satisfy all the requirements for Grade A classification.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">satisfy all the requirements for Grade A classification</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0019">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">If such minimum regulatory
requirements are not publicly disclosed or otherwise made available by the counterparty bank then the
counterparty bank must be assessed as Grade C.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">must be assessed as Grade C</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0019">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if minimum regulatory requirements are not publicly disclosed or otherwise made available by the counterparty bank</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0020">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">At a minimum, if any of the following triggers is breached, a bank must classify the exposure into
Grade C:
• The counterparty bank does not meet the criteria for being classifed as Grade B with respect to
its published minimum regulatory requirements, as set out in paragraphs 25 and 26;</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">classify the exposure into Grade C</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0020">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if the counterparty bank does not meet the criteria for being classified as Grade B with respect to its published minimum regulatory requirements, as set out in paragraphs 25 and 26</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0021">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In that case, the exposure to such counterparty bank must be classified into
Grade C.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">must be classified into Grade C</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the exposure to such counterparty bank">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the exposure to such counterparty bank</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0021">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">In that case</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0022">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Proceeds deriving from the issue of these
bonds must be invested in conformity with the law in assets which, during the whole period of the validity
of the bonds, are capable of covering claims attached to the bonds and which, in the event of the failure
of the issuer, would be used on a priority basis for the reimbursement of the principal and payment of the
accrued interest.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">Invest proceeds from the bond issue in conformity with the law in assets that cover bond-related claims and are available on a priority basis for reimbursement of principal and accrued interest in case of issuer failure</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Issuer of the bonds">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Issuer of the bonds</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0022">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">During the whole period of the validity of the bonds</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0023">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In order to be eligible for the risk weights set out in paragraph 35, the underlying assets (the
cover pool) of covered bonds as defined in paragraph 32 shall meet the requirements set out in paragraph
34 and shall include any of the following:
• claims on, or guaranteed by, sovereigns, their central banks, public sector entities or multilateral
development banks;</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">meet the requirements set out in paragraph 34 and shall include any of the following: claims on, or guaranteed by, sovereigns, their central banks, public sector entities or multilateral development banks</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:underlying assets (the cover pool) of covered bonds">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">underlying assets (the cover pool) of covered bonds</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0023">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in order to be eligible for the risk weights set out in paragraph 35</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0024">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The conditions set out in this paragraph must be satisfied at the inception of the covered bond
and throughout its remaining maturity.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">satisfy the conditions set out in this paragraph</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:covered bond">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">covered bond</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0024">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">at the inception of the covered bond and throughout its remaining maturity</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0025">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Covered bonds that meet the criteria set out in the paragraphs 33 and 34 shall be risk-weighted
based on the issue-specific rating or the issuer’s risk weight according to the rules outlined in paragraphs
98 to 116.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">shall be risk-weighted based on the issue-specific rating or the issuer’s risk weight</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Covered bonds">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Covered bonds</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0025">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">that meet the criteria set out in paragraphs 33 and 34</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0026">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For covered bonds with issue-specific ratings,21 the risk weight shall be determined according
to Table 8.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">the risk weight shall be determined according to Table 8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:covered bonds with issue-specific ratings">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">covered bonds with issue-specific ratings</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0027">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must perform due diligence to ensure that the external ratings appropriately and
conservatively reflect the creditworthiness of the covered bond and the issuing bank.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">perform due diligence to ensure that the external ratings appropriately and conservatively reflect the creditworthiness of the covered bond and the issuing bank</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0028">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A+ to A– etc), the bank must assign a risk weight at least one bucket higher than the
“base” risk weight determined by the external rating.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">assign a risk weight at least one bucket higher than the 'base' risk weight determined by the external rating</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0028">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if the external rating is A+ to A– etc</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0029">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Due diligence analysis must never result in the
application of a lower risk weight than that determined by the external rating.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">must not result in the application of a lower risk weight than that determined by the external rating</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0030">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For corporate exposures of banks incorporated in jurisdictions that allow the use of external
ratings for regulatory purposes, banks will assign “base” risk weights according to Table 10.22 Banks must
perform due diligence to ensure that the external ratings appropriately and conservatively reflect the
creditworthiness of the counterparties.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">assign 'base' risk weights according to Table 10.22 and perform due diligence to ensure that the external ratings appropriately and conservatively reflect the creditworthiness of the counterparties</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:banks incorporated in jurisdictions that allow the use of external ratings for regulatory purposes">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">banks incorporated in jurisdictions that allow the use of external ratings for regulatory purposes</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0030">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for corporate exposures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0031">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks which have assigned risk weights to their rated bank
exposures based on paragraph 18 must assign risk weights for all their corporate exposures according to
Table 10.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">assign risk weights for all their corporate exposures according to Table 10</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0031">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">which have assigned risk weights to their rated bank exposures based on paragraph 18</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0032">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A+ to A– etc), the bank must assign a risk weight at least
one bucket higher than the “base” risk weight determined by the external rating.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">assign a risk weight at least one bucket higher than the 'base' risk weight determined by the external rating</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0032">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if the external rating is A+ to A– etc</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0033">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Due diligence analysis
must never result in the application of a lower risk weight than that determined by the external rating.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">must never result in the application of a lower risk weight than that determined by the external rating</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0034">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must apply the treatment set out in this paragraph to their corporate exposures if they
have assigned risk weights to their rated bank exposures based on paragraph 21.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">apply the treatment set out in this paragraph to their corporate exposures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0034">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if they have assigned risk weights to their rated bank exposures based on paragraph 21</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0035">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Moreover, the corporate entity
(or its parent company) must have securities outstanding on a recognised securities exchange.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">must have securities outstanding on a recognised securities exchange</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:corporate entity (or its parent company)">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
