    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0039">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">paragraph 107 does not apply</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0040">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For this
purpose, operational phase is defined as the phase in which the entity that was specifically
created to finance the project has (i) a positive net cash flow that is sufficient to cover any
remaining contractual obligation, and (ii) declining long term debt.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">have a positive net cash flow that is sufficient to cover any remaining contractual obligation and declining long term debt</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the entity that was specifically created to finance the project">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the entity that was specifically created to finance the project</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0040">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">during the operational phase</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0041">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The following conditions must
also be met:
• The project finance entity is restricted from acting to the detriment of the creditors (eg by not
being able to issue additional debt without the consent of existing creditors);</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">is restricted from acting to the detriment of the creditors</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The project finance entity">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The project finance entity</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0041">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">e.g., by not being able to issue additional debt without the consent of existing creditors</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0042">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The project finance entity’s revenue depends on one main counterparty and this main
counterparty shall be a central government, PSE or a corporate entity with a risk weight of 80%
or lower;</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure revenue depends only on a main counterparty that is a central government, PSE, or corporate entity with a risk weight of 80% or lower</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:project finance entity">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">project finance entity</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0042">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if the project finance entity's revenue depends on one main counterparty</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0042">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">80%</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0043">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• It does not embody an obligation on the part of the issuer;</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">embody an obligation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:issuer">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">issuer</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0044">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Additionally any of the following instruments must be categorised as an equity exposure:
23 Availability-based revenues mean that once construction is completed, the project finance entity is entitled to payments from
its contractual counterparties (eg the government), as long as contract conditions are fulfilled.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">be entitled to payments from its contractual counterparties</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0044">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">once construction is completed and contract conditions are fulfilled</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0045">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• An instrument that embodies an obligation on the part of the issuer and meets any of the
following conditions:
1) The issuer may defer indefinitely the settlement of the obligation;</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">defer indefinitely the settlement of the obligation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0045">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">instrument embodies an obligation on the part of the issuer</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0046">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">2) The obligation requires (or permits at the issuer’s discretion) settlement by issuance of
a fixed number of the issuer’s equity shares;</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">settlement by issuance of a fixed number of the issuer’s equity shares</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0046">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">The obligation requires (or permits at the issuer’s discretion)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0047">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">3) The obligation requires (or permits at the issuer’s discretion) settlement by issuance of
a variable number of the issuer’s equity shares and (ceteris paribus) any change in the
value of the obligation is attributable to, comparable to, and in the same direction as,
the change in the value of a fixed number of the issuer’s equity shares;25 or,
4) The holder has the option to require that the obligation be settled in equity shares,
unless either (i) in the case of a traded instrument, the supervisor is content that the
bank has demonstrated that the instrument trades more like the debt of the issuer than
like its equity, or (ii) in the case of non-traded instruments, the supervisor is content
that the bank has demonstrated that the instrument should be treated as a debt
position.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">settlement by issuance of a variable number of the issuer’s equity shares</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0047">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">any change in the value of the obligation is attributable to, comparable to, and in the same direction as, the change in the value of a fixed number of the issuer’s equity shares</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0048">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Debt obligations and other securities, partnerships, derivatives or other vehicles structured with
the intent of conveying the economic substance of equity ownership are considered an equity holding.26
This includes liabilities from which the return is linked to that of equities.27 Conversely, equity investments
that are structured with the intent of conveying the economic substance of debt holdings or securitisation
exposures would not be considered an equity holding.28
25 For certain obligations that require or permit settlement by issuance of a variable number of the issuer’s equity shares, the
change in the monetary value of the obligation is equal to the change in the fair value of a fixed number of equity shares
multiplied by a specified factor.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">are considered an equity holding if structured with the intent of conveying the economic substance of equity ownership</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Debt obligations and other securities, partnerships, derivatives or other vehicles">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Debt obligations and other securities, partnerships, derivatives or other vehicles</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0048">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">intent of conveying the economic substance of equity ownership</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0048">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">equity investments structured with the intent of conveying the economic substance of debt holdings or securitisation exposures would not be considered an equity holding</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0049">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For example, an issuer may be required to settle an obligation by issuing shares with a value equal to three
times the appreciation in the fair value of 1,000 equity shares.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">settle an obligation by issuing shares</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0049">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">fair value appreciation of 1,000 equity shares</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0049">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">value equal to three times the appreciation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0050">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">That obligation is considered to be the same as an obligation
that requires settlement by issuance of shares equal to the appreciation in the fair value of 3,000 equity shares.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">settlement by issuance of shares equal to the appreciation in the fair value of 3,000 equity shares</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0050">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">obligation is considered to be the same as an obligation that requires settlement by issuance of shares</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0050">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">3000</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0051">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">To apply the risk-weights in Tables 11, 12, 13 and 14 and the approaches set out in paragraphs
65 and 71, the loan must meet the following requirements:
• Finished property: the property securing the exposure must be fully completed.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">meet the following requirements to apply the risk-weights in Tables 11, 12, 13 and 14 and the approaches set out in paragraphs 65 and 71</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the loan">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the loan</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0051">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to apply the risk-weights in Tables 11, 12, 13 and 14 and the approaches set out in paragraphs 65 and 71</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0052">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The calculation must be done on the portfolio
of retail exposures that meet the product and orientation criteria as well as the low value of the exposure.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">must be done on the portfolio of retail exposures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The calculation">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The calculation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0052">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">that meet the product and orientation criteria as well as the low value of the exposure</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0053">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">or (ii) where the sovereign or PSEs involved have the legal powers and ability to
ensure that the property under construction will be finished.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure that the property under construction will be finished</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:sovereign or PSEs">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">sovereign or PSEs</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0053">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where the sovereign or PSEs involved have the legal powers and ability</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0054">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• Legal enforceability: any claim on the property taken must be legally enforceable in all relevant
jurisdictions.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">be legally enforceable</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:any claim on the property taken">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">any claim on the property taken</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0054">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in all relevant jurisdictions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0055">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The collateral agreement and the legal process underpinning it must be such that
they provide for the bank to realise the value of the property within a reasonable time frame.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">realise the value of the property within a reasonable time frame</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0055">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">the collateral agreement and the legal process underpinning it</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0055">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">within a reasonable time frame</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0056">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">and (ii) where the sale of the property is not carried out by means
of a public auction, entities holding a senior lien take reasonable steps to obtain a fair market
value or the best price that may be obtained in the circumstances when exercising any power of
sale on their own (ie it is not possible for the entity holding the senior lien to sell the property on
its own at a discounted value in detriment of the junior lien).35
• Ability of the borrower to repay: the borrower must meet the requirements set according to
paragraph 61.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">take reasonable steps to obtain a fair market value or the best price that may be obtained in the circumstances when exercising any power of sale on their own</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:entities holding a senior lien">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">entities holding a senior lien</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0056">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where the sale of the property is not carried out by means of a public auction</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0056">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">it is not possible for the entity holding the senior lien to sell the property on its own at a discounted value in detriment of the junior lien</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0057">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• Prudent value of property: the property must be valued according to the criteria in paragraph 62
for determining the value in the loan to value (LTV) ratio.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">must be valued according to the criteria in paragraph 62 for determining the value in the loan to value (LTV) ratio</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the property">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the property</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0057">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for determining the value in the loan to value (LTV) ratio</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0058">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Moreover, the value of the property
must not depend materially on the performance of the borrower.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">must not depend materially on the performance of the borrower</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the value of the property">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the value of the property</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0059">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Instead, they are typically provided as loans that are guaranteed by a highly rated monoline guarantor
that is required to repay the bank in full if the borrower defaults, and where the bank has legal right to take a mortgage on the
property in the event that the guarantor fails.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">repay the bank in full if the borrower defaults</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:highly rated monoline guarantor">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">highly rated monoline guarantor</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0059">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if the borrower defaults</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0060">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">These loans may be treated as residential real estate exposures (rather than
guaranteed loans) if the following additional conditions are met:
(i) the borrower shall be contractually committed not to grant any mortgage lien without the consent of the bank that
granted the loan;</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">shall be contractually committed not to grant any mortgage lien without the consent of the bank that granted the loan</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:borrower">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">borrower</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0060">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if the following additional conditions are met</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0061">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">(ii) the guarantor shall be either a bank or a financial institution subject to capital requirements comparable to those applied
to banks or an insurance undertaking;</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">shall be either a bank or a financial institution subject to capital requirements comparable to those applied to banks or an insurance undertaking</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the guarantor">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the guarantor</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0062">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">(iii) the guarantor shall establish a fully-funded mutual guarantee fund or equivalent protection for insurance undertakings
to absorb credit risk losses, whose calibration shall be periodically reviewed by its supervisors and subject to periodic
stress testing;</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">establish a fully-funded mutual guarantee fund or equivalent protection for insurance undertakings to absorb credit risk losses</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0062">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">whose calibration shall be periodically reviewed by its supervisors and subject to periodic stress testing</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0063">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">and
(iv) the bank shall be contractually and legally allowed to take a mortgage on the property in the event that the guarantor
fails.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">be contractually and legally allowed to take a mortgage on the property</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0063">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">the guarantor fails</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0064">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Basel III: Finalising post-crisis reforms 19
• Required documentation: all the information required at loan origination and for monitoring
purposes must be properly documented, including information on the ability of the borrower to
repay and on the valuation of the property.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">properly document all information required at loan origination and for monitoring purposes</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:banks or financial institutions">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">banks or financial institutions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0064">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">at loan origination and for monitoring purposes</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0065">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">National supervisors should ensure that banks put in place underwriting policies with respect to
the granting of mortgage loans that include the assessment of the ability of the borrower to repay.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure that banks put in place underwriting policies with respect to the granting of mortgage loans that include the assessment of the ability of the borrower to repay</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:National supervisors">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">National supervisors</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0066">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Underwriting policies must define a metric(s) (such as the loan’s debt service coverage ratio) and specify
its (their) corresponding relevant level(s) to conduct such assessment.36 Underwriting policies must also
be appropriate when the repayment of the mortgage loan depends materially on the cash flows generated
by the property, including relevant metrics (such as an occupancy rate of the property).</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">define a metric(s) and specify its (their) corresponding relevant level(s) to conduct assessment; be appropriate when repayment of the mortgage loan depends materially on the cash flows generated by the property</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Underwriting policies">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Underwriting policies</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0066">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when the repayment of the mortgage loan depends materially on the cash flows generated by the property</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0066">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">such as an occupancy rate of the property</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0067">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The value of the
property will be maintained at the value measured at origination unless national supervisors elect to
require banks to revise the property value downward.37 The value must be adjusted if an extraordinary,
idiosyncratic event occurs resulting in a permanent reduction of the property value.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">adjust the value of the property</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0067">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">an extraordinary, idiosyncratic event occurs resulting in a permanent reduction of the property value</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0067">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">unless national supervisors elect to require banks to revise the property value downward</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0068">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The LTV ratio must be prudently calculated in accordance with the following requirements:
• Amount of the loan: includes the outstanding loan amount and any undrawn committed amount
of the mortgage loan.38 The loan amount must be calculated gross of any provisions and other
risk mitigants, except for pledged deposits accounts with the lending bank that meet all
requirements for on-balance sheet netting and have been unconditionally and irrevocably
pledged for the sole purposes of redemption of the mortgage loan.39
36 Metrics and levels for measuring the ability to repay should mirror the FSB Principles for sound residential mortgage
underwriting practices (April 2012).</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">prudently calculate the LTV ratio</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The entity calculating the LTV ratio">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The entity calculating the LTV ratio</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0068">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when determining the amount of the loan</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0068">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">pledged deposit accounts with the lending bank that meet all requirements for on-balance sheet netting and have been unconditionally and irrevocably pledged for the sole purposes of redemption of the mortgage loan</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0069">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">39 In jurisdictions where junior liens held by a different bank than that holding the senior lien are recognised (in accordance
with paragraph 60), the loan amount of the junior liens must include all other loans secured with liens of equal or higher
ranking than the bank’s lien securing the loan for purposes of defining the LTV bucket and risk weight for the junior lien.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">include all other loans secured with liens of equal or higher ranking than the bank’s lien securing the loan for purposes of defining the LTV bucket and risk weight for the junior lien</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:banks holding junior liens">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">banks holding junior liens</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0069">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in jurisdictions where junior liens held by a different bank than that holding the senior lien are recognised (in accordance with paragraph 60)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0070">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">20 Basel III: Finalising post-crisis reforms
• Value of the property: the valuation must be appraised independently40 using prudently
conservative valuation criteria.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">appraise the value of the property independently using prudently conservative valuation criteria</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0070">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when determining the value of the property</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0071">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">To ensure that the value of the property is appraised in a prudently
conservative manner, the valuation must exclude expectations on price increases and must be
adjusted to take into account the potential for the current market price to be significantly above
the value that would be sustainable over the life of the loan.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">exclude expectations on price increases and be adjusted to take into account the potential for the current market price to be significantly above the value that would be sustainable over the life of the loan</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the valuation">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the valuation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0071">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to ensure that the value of the property is appraised in a prudently conservative manner</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0072">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">however, the LTV bucket and risk weight to be applied to the exposure amount must
be determined before the application of the appropriate credit risk mitigation technique.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">determine the LTV bucket and risk weight to be applied to the exposure amount</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the entity determining the LTV bucket and risk weight">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the entity determining the LTV bucket and risk weight</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0072">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">before the application of the appropriate credit risk mitigation technique</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0073">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For example, for a loan of €70,000 to an
40 The valuation must be done independently from the bank’s mortgage acquisition, loan processing and loan decision process.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">must be done independently from the bank’s mortgage acquisition, loan processing and loan decision process</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The valuation">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The valuation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0074">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• pre-sale or pre-lease contracts amount to a signficant portion of total contracts or substantial
equity at risk.52 Pre-sale or pre-lease contracts must be legally binding written contracts and the
purchaser/renter must have made a substantial cash deposit which is subject to forfeiture if the
contract is terminated.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">must be legally binding written contracts and the purchaser/renter must have made a substantial cash deposit which is subject to forfeiture if the contract is terminated</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:pre-sale or pre-lease contracts">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">pre-sale or pre-lease contracts</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0074">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">pre-sale or pre-lease contracts amount to a significant portion of total contracts or substantial equity at risk</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0075">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">49 For such exposures, national supervisors may allow banks to apply the treatment described in paragraphs 70 to 71 subject to
the following conditions: (i) the losses stemming from commercial real estate lending up to 60% of LTV must not exceed 0.3%
of the outstanding loans in any given year and (ii) overall losses stemming from commercial real estate lending must not exceed
0.5% of the outstanding loans in any given year.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">allow banks to apply the treatment described in paragraphs 70 to 71</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:national supervisors">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">national supervisors</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0075">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">the losses stemming from commercial real estate lending up to 60% of LTV must not exceed 0.3% of the outstanding loans in any given year and overall losses stemming from commercial real estate lending must not exceed 0.5% of the outstanding loans in any given year</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0076">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Jurisdictions applying
such treatment must publicly disclose whether these conditions are met.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">publicly disclose whether these conditions are met</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Jurisdictions applying such treatment">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Jurisdictions applying such treatment</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0076">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">applying such treatment</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0077">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">It also includes any such arrangement that can
be cancelled by the bank if the obligor fails to meet conditions set out in the facility documentation,
including conditions that must be met by the obligor prior to any initial or subsequent drawdown under
the arrangement.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">cancel the arrangement</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0077">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">the obligor fails to meet conditions set out in the facility documentation, including conditions that must be met prior to any initial or subsequent drawdown</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0078">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">(ii) the
client is required to apply to the bank for the initial and each subsequent drawdown;</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">apply to the bank for the initial and each subsequent drawdown</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:client">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">client</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0079">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The risk-weighting treatment for
counterparty credit risk must be applied in addition to the credit risk charge on the securities or
posted collateral, where the credit risk of the securities lent or posted as collateral remains with
the bank.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">apply the risk-weighting treatment for counterparty credit risk in addition to the credit risk charge on the securities or posted collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0079">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where the credit risk of the securities lent or posted as collateral remains with the bank</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0080">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must closely monitor securities, commodities and foreign exchange transactions that have
failed, starting from the first day they fail.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">closely monitor securities, commodities and foreign exchange transactions that have failed</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0080">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">starting from the first day they fail</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0081">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A capital charge on failed transactions must be calculated in
accordance with Annex 3 of the Basel II framework (June 2006).</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">must be calculated in accordance with Annex 3 of the Basel II framework (June 2006)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:A capital charge on failed transactions">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">A capital charge on failed transactions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0082">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Irrespective of the booking or the accounting of the transaction,
unsettled transactions must be taken into account for regulatory capital requirements purposes.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">take into account unsettled transactions for regulatory capital requirements purposes</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Financial institutions">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Financial institutions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0082">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">irrespective of the booking or the accounting of the transaction</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0083">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Furthermore, when such transactions
are not processed through a delivery-versus-payment (DvP) or payment-versus-payment (PvP)
mechanism, banks must calculate a capital charge as set forth in Annex 3 of the Basel II framework (June
2006).</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">calculate a capital charge as set forth in Annex 3 of the Basel II framework (June 2006)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0083">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when such transactions are not processed through a delivery-versus-payment (DvP) or payment-versus-payment (PvP) mechanism</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0084">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For first-to-default credit derivatives, the
risk weights of the assets included in the basket must be aggregated up to a maximum of 1250% and
multiplied by the nominal amount of the protection provided by the credit derivative to obtain the risk-
weighted asset amount.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">Aggregate the risk weights of the assets included in the basket up to a maximum of 1250% and multiply by the nominal amount of the protection provided by the credit derivative to obtain the risk-weighted asset amount</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Institutions holding first-to-default credit derivatives">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Institutions holding first-to-default credit derivatives</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0084">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">For first-to-default credit derivatives</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0084">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">1250%</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0085">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A defaulted
borrower is a borrower in respect of whom any of the following events have occurred:
• Any material credit obligation that is past due for more than 90 days.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">be classified as defaulted</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0085">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">any material credit obligation is past due for more than 90 days</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0085">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">90 days</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0086">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• Any material credit obligation is on non-accrued status (eg the lending bank no longer recognises
accrued interest as income or, if recognised, makes an equivalent amount of provisions);</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">place any material credit obligation on non-accrued status and no longer recognise accrued interest as income or make an equivalent amount of provisions if interest is recognised</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:lending bank">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">lending bank</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0086">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when a material credit obligation is on non-accrued status</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0087">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• Any credit obligation is sold at a material credit-related economic loss;</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">sell credit obligation at a material credit-related economic loss</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Any credit obligation seller">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Any credit obligation seller</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0087">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">material credit-related economic loss</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0088">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• A distressed restructuring of any credit obligation (ie a restructuring that may result in a
diminished financial obligation caused by the material forgiveness, or postponement, of principal,
interest or (where relevant) fees) is agreed by the bank;</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">agree to a distressed restructuring of any credit obligation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0088">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">a restructuring that may result in a diminished financial obligation caused by the material forgiveness, or postponement, of principal, interest or (where relevant) fees</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0089">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For retail exposures, the definition of default can be applied at the level of a particular credit
obligation, rather than at the level of the borrower.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">apply the definition of default at the level of a particular credit obligation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:retail exposures">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">retail exposures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0089">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">rather than at the level of the borrower</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0090">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">As such, default by a borrower on one obligation does
not require a bank to treat all other obligations to the banking group as defaulted.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">treat all other obligations to the banking group as defaulted</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0090">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">default by a borrower on one obligation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0090">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">a bank is not required to treat all other obligations as defaulted</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0091">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">With the exception of residential real estate exposures treated under paragraph 93, the unsecured
or unguaranteed portion of a defaulted exposure shall be risk-weighted net of specific provisions and
partial write-offs as follows:
• 150% risk weight when specific provisions are less than 20% of the outstanding amount of the
loan;</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">risk-weight the unsecured or unguaranteed portion of a defaulted exposure net of specific provisions and partial write-offs</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:regulated institutions">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">regulated institutions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0091">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">defaulted exposure, excluding residential real estate exposures treated under paragraph 93</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0091">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">150% risk weight when specific provisions are less than 20% of the outstanding amount of the loan</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0091">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">residential real estate exposures treated under paragraph 93</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0092">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Defaulted residential real estate exposures where repayments do not materially depend on cash
flows generated by the property securing the loan shall be risk-weighted net of specific provisions and
partial write-offs at 100%.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">shall be risk-weighted net of specific provisions and partial write-offs at 100%</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Defaulted residential real estate exposures">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Defaulted residential real estate exposures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0092">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where repayments do not materially depend on cash flows generated by the property securing the loan</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0092">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">100%</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0093">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">An ECAI must satisfy each of the following eight criteria.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">satisfy each of the following eight criteria</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:ECAI">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">ECAI</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0093">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0094">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• Objectivity: The methodology for assigning external ratings must be rigorous, systematic, and
subject to some form of validation based on historical experience.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">must be rigorous, systematic, and subject to some form of validation based on historical experience</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The methodology for assigning external ratings">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The methodology for assigning external ratings</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0095">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Moreover, external ratings
must be subject to ongoing review and responsive to changes in financial condition.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">must be subject to ongoing review and responsive to changes in financial condition</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:external ratings">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">external ratings</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0096">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Before being
recognised by supervisors, a rating methodology for each market segment, including rigorous
backtesting, must have been established for at least one year and preferably three years.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">must have been established for at least one year and preferably three years</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:rating methodology for each market segment">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">rating methodology for each market segment</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0096">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">before being recognised by supervisors</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0096">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">at least one year and preferably three years</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0097">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">60 At a minimum, the following situations and their influence on the ECAI’s credit rating methodologies or credit rating actions
shall be disclosed:
• The ECAI is being paid to issue a credit rating by the rated entity or by the obligor, originator, underwriter, or arranger of
the rated obligation;</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">disclose the situation and its influence on the ECAI’s credit rating methodologies or credit rating actions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0097">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">the ECAI is being paid to issue a credit rating by the rated entity or by the obligor, originator, underwriter, or arranger of the rated obligation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0098">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In particular, ECAIs
should assign analysts with appropriate knowledge and experience to assess the creditworthiness
of the type of entity or obligation being rated.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">assign analysts with appropriate knowledge and experience to assess the creditworthiness of the type of entity or obligation being rated</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:ECAIs">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">ECAIs</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0099">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• No abuse of unsolicited ratings: ECAIs must not use unsolicited ratings to put pressure on
entities to obtain solicited ratings.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">must not use unsolicited ratings to put pressure on entities to obtain solicited ratings</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0099">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when using unsolicited ratings</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0100">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must use the chosen ECAIs and their ratings consistently for all types of claim where they
have been recognised by their supervisor as an eligible ECAI, for both risk-weighting and risk management
purposes.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">use the chosen ECAIs and their ratings consistently for all types of claim</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0100">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where they have been recognised by their supervisor as an eligible ECAI, for both risk-weighting and risk management purposes</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0101">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Whether the bank intends to rely on an issuer- or an issue-specific rating, the rating must take
into account and reflect the entire amount of credit risk exposure the bank has with regard to all payments
owed to it.62
62 For example, if a bank is owed both principal and interest, the assessment must fully take into account and reflect the credit
risk associated with repayment of both principal and interest.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">take into account and reflect the entire amount of credit risk exposure with regard to all payments owed to it in the rating</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0101">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">whether the bank intends to rely on an issuer- or an issue-specific rating</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0102">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">To qualify, MDBs must have preferred creditor status recognised in the market and be
included in footnote 11 (in paragraph 14).</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">have preferred creditor status recognised in the market and be included in footnote 11 (in paragraph 14)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0102">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to qualify</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0103">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">No transaction in which CRM techniques are used shall receive a higher capital requirement than
an otherwise identical transaction where such techniques are not used.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">shall not receive a higher capital requirement when CRM techniques are used</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:transaction">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">transaction</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0103">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when CRM techniques are used compared to an otherwise identical transaction where such techniques are not used</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0104">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The Pillar 3 requirements must be fulfilled for banks to obtain capital relief in respect of any CRM
techniques.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">fulfill the Pillar 3 requirements</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0104">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to obtain capital relief in respect of any CRM techniques</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0105">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The effects of CRM must not be double-counted.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">must not be double-counted</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The effects of CRM">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The effects of CRM</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0106">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Therefore,
banks must employ robust procedures and processes to control these risks, including strategy;</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">employ robust procedures and processes to control these risks, including strategy</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0106">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to control these risks</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0107">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In order for CRM techniques to provide protection, the credit quality of the counterparty must
not have a material positive correlation with the employed CRM technique or with the resulting residual
risks (as defined in paragraph 122).</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">must not have a material positive correlation with the credit quality of the counterparty</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:CRM techniques">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">CRM techniques</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0107">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in order to provide protection</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0108">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In the case where a bank has multiple CRM techniques covering a single exposure (eg a bank has
both collateral and a guarantee partially covering an exposure), the bank must subdivide the exposure
into portions covered by each type of CRM technique (eg portion covered by collateral, portion covered
by guarantee) and the risk-weighted assets of each portion must be calculated separately.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">subdivide the exposure into portions covered by each type of CRM technique and calculate the risk-weighted assets of each portion separately</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0108">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where a bank has multiple CRM techniques covering a single exposure</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0109">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">When credit
protection provided by a single protection provider has differing maturities, they must be subdivided into
separate protection as well.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">must be subdivided into separate protection</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:credit protection provided by a single protection provider">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">credit protection provided by a single protection provider</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0109">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when credit protection has differing maturities</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0110">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In order for banks to obtain capital relief for any use of CRM techniques, all documentation used
in collateralised transactions, on-balance sheet netting agreements, guarantees and credit derivatives
must be binding on all parties and legally enforceable in all relevant jurisdictions.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure all documentation used in collateralised transactions, on-balance sheet netting agreements, guarantees and credit derivatives is binding on all parties and legally enforceable in all relevant jurisdictions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0110">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in order to obtain capital relief for any use of CRM techniques</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0111">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must have
conducted sufficient legal review to verify this and have a well-founded legal basis to reach this conclusion,
and undertake such further review as necessary to ensure continuing enforceability.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">conduct sufficient legal review to verify this and have a well-founded legal basis to reach this conclusion, and undertake further review as necessary to ensure continuing enforceability</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0111">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to verify this and ensure continuing enforceability</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0112">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The maturity of the underlying exposure and the maturity of the hedge must both be defined
conservatively.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">define the maturity of the underlying exposure and the maturity of the hedge conservatively</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0113">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The effective maturity of the underlying must be gauged as the longest possible remaining
time before the counterparty is scheduled to fulfil its obligation, taking into account any applicable grace
period.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">gauge the effective maturity of the underlying as the longest possible remaining time before the counterparty is scheduled to fulfil its obligation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The regulated entity assessing effective maturity">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The regulated entity assessing effective maturity</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0113">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">taking into account any applicable grace period</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0114">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For the hedge, (embedded) options that may reduce the term of the hedge must be taken into
account so that the shortest possible effective maturity is used.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">take into account (embedded) options that may reduce the term of the hedge</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:hedge">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">hedge</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0114">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if the options may reduce the term of the hedge</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0115">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Before capital relief is granted in respect of any form of collateral, the standards set out below in
paragraphs 140 to 145 must be met, irrespective of whether the simple or the comprehensive approach is
used.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">Meet the standards set out in paragraphs 140 to 145</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Regulated entity granting capital relief">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Regulated entity granting capital relief</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0115">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">Before capital relief is granted in respect of any form of collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0116">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks that lend securities or post collateral must calculate capital requirements for both of the
following: (i) the credit risk or market risk of the securities, if this remains with the bank;</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">calculate capital requirements for the credit risk or market risk of the securities</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Banks that lend securities or post collateral">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Banks that lend securities or post collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0116">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if the credit risk or market risk of the securities remains with the bank</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0117">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The legal mechanism by which collateral is pledged or transferred must ensure that the bank has
the right to liquidate or take legal possession of it, in a timely manner, in the event of the default,
insolvency or bankruptcy (or one or more otherwise-defined credit events set out in the transaction
documentation) of the counterparty (and, where applicable, of the custodian holding the collateral).</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure the right to liquidate or take legal possession of collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0117">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in the event of the default, insolvency or bankruptcy (or one or more otherwise-defined credit events set out in the transaction documentation) of the counterparty (and, where applicable, of the custodian holding the collateral)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0117">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">in a timely manner</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0118">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Additionally, banks must take all steps necessary to fulfil those requirements under the law applicable to
the bank’s interest in the collateral for obtaining and maintaining an enforceable security interest, eg by
registering it with a registrar, or for exercising a right to net or set off in relation to the title transfer of the
collateral.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">take all steps necessary to fulfil those requirements under the law applicable to the bank’s interest in the collateral for obtaining and maintaining an enforceable security interest, e.g. by registering it with a registrar, or for exercising a right to net or set off in relation to the title transfer of the collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0118">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">under the law applicable to the bank’s interest in the collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0119">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must have clear and robust procedures for the timely liquidation of collateral to ensure
that any legal conditions required for declaring the default of the counterparty and liquidating the
collateral are observed, and that collateral can be liquidated promptly.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">have clear and robust procedures for the timely liquidation of collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0119">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to ensure that any legal conditions required for declaring the default of the counterparty and liquidating the collateral are observed, and that collateral can be liquidated promptly</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0120">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must ensure that sufficient resources are devoted to the orderly operation of margin
agreements with OTC derivative and securities-financing counterparties, as measured by the timeliness
and accuracy of its outgoing margin calls and response time to incoming margin calls.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure that sufficient resources are devoted to the orderly operation of margin agreements with OTC derivative and securities-financing counterparties</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0120">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">as measured by the timeliness and accuracy of its outgoing margin calls and response time to incoming margin calls</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0121">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must have
collateral risk management policies in place to control, monitor and report:
• the risk to which margin agreements expose them (such as the volatility and liquidity of the
securities exchanged as collateral);</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">have collateral risk management policies in place to control, monitor and report the risk to which margin agreements expose them</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0121">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">the risk associated with margin agreements, such as the volatility and liquidity of the securities exchanged as collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0122">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Where the collateral is held by a custodian, banks must take reasonable steps to ensure that the
custodian segregates the collateral from its own assets.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">take reasonable steps to ensure that the custodian segregates the collateral from its own assets</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0122">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where the collateral is held by a custodian</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0123">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A capital requirement must be applied on both sides of a transaction.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">apply a capital requirement on both sides of a transaction</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Regulated financial institution">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Regulated financial institution</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0124">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In such circumstances,
a bank must calculate capital requirements as if it were itself the principal.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">calculate capital requirements as if it were itself the principal</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0124">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in such circumstances</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0125">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For collateral to be recognised in the simple approach, it must be pledged for at least the life of
the exposure and it must be marked to market and revalued with a minimum frequency of six months.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">be pledged for at least the life of the exposure and be marked to market and revalued</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:collateral">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0125">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to be recognised in the simple approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0125">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">minimum frequency of six months</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0126">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The remainder of the
exposure must be assigned the risk weight appropriate to the counterparty.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">must be assigned the risk weight appropriate to the counterparty</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The remainder of the exposure">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The remainder of the exposure</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0127">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">71 However, the use or potential use by a UCITS/mutual fund of derivative instruments solely to hedge investments listed in this
paragraph and paragraph 159 shall not prevent units in that UCITS/mutual fund from being eligible financial collateral.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">use or potential use of derivative instruments solely to hedge investments</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:UCITS/mutual fund">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">UCITS/mutual fund</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0127">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">investments listed in this paragraph and paragraph 159</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0127">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">units in that UCITS/mutual fund shall not be prevented from being eligible financial collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0128">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">(g) The transaction is governed by documentation specifying that if the counterparty fails to satisfy
an obligation to deliver cash or securities or to deliver margin or otherwise defaults, then the
transaction is immediately terminable;</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">is immediately terminable if the counterparty fails to satisfy an obligation to deliver cash or securities or to deliver margin or otherwise defaults</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The transaction">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The transaction</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0128">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if the counterparty fails to satisfy an obligation to deliver cash or securities or to deliver margin or otherwise defaults</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0128">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">immediately</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0129">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In the comprehensive approach, when taking collateral, banks must calculate their adjusted
exposure to a counterparty in order to take account of the risk mitigating effect of that collateral.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">calculate their adjusted exposure to a counterparty</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0129">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when taking collateral in the comprehensive approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0130">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks
must use the applicable supervisory haircuts to adjust both the amount of the exposure to the
counterparty and the value of any collateral received in support of that counterparty to take account of
possible future fluctuations in the value of either,72 as occasioned by market movements.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">use the applicable supervisory haircuts to adjust both the amount of the exposure to the counterparty and the value of any collateral received</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0130">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to take account of possible future fluctuations in the value of either, as occasioned by market movements</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0131">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Haircuts must be scaled up using the square root of time formula depending on the frequency of
remargining or marking to market.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">must be scaled up using the square root of time formula</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Haircuts">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Haircuts</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0131">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">depending on the frequency of remargining or marking to market</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0132">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Additionally, where the exposure and collateral are held in different currencies, banks must apply
an additional haircut to the volatility-adjusted collateral amount in accordance with paragraphs 165
and 204 to take account of possible future fluctuations in exchange rates.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">apply an additional haircut to the volatility-adjusted collateral amount</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0132">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where the exposure and collateral are held in different currencies</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0132">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">in accordance with paragraphs 165 and 204</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0133">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In the case of maturity mismatches, the value of the collateral received (collateral amount) must
be adjusted in accordance with paragraphs 126 to 130.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">adjust the value of the collateral received</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the entity holding collateral">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the entity holding collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0133">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in the case of maturity mismatches</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0134">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The exposure amount after risk mitigation (E*) must be multiplied by the risk weight of the
counterparty to obtain the risk-weighted asset amount for the collateralised transaction.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">multiply the exposure amount after risk mitigation (E*) by the risk weight of the counterparty</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:regulated entity calculating risk-weighted assets">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">regulated entity calculating risk-weighted assets</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0134">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for a collateralised transaction</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0135">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In jurisdictions that allow the use of external ratings for regulatory purposes, the following
supervisory haircuts (assuming daily mark-to-market, daily remargining and a 10-business day holding
period), expressed as percentages, must be used to determine the haircuts appropriate to the collateral
(Hc) and to the exposure (He):
40 Basel III: Finalising post-crisis reforms
Supervisory haircuts for comprehensive approach
Jurisdictions that allow the use of external ratings for regulatory purposes Table 14
Issue rating for debt Securitisation
Residual maturity Sovereigns73 Other issuers74
securities exposures75
≤ 1 year 0.5 1 2
&gt;1 year, ≤ 3 years 2 3 8
AAA to AA–/A-1 &gt;3 years, ≤ 5 years 4
&gt;5 years, ≤ 10 years 4 6 16
&gt; 10 years 12
≤ 1 year 1 2 4
A+ to BBB–/
&gt;1 year, ≤ 3 years 3 4 12
A-2/A-3/P-3 and
unrated bank &gt;3 years, ≤ 5 years 6
securities per para.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">use the specified supervisory haircuts to determine the haircuts appropriate to the collateral (Hc) and to the exposure (He)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Jurisdictions that allow the use of external ratings for regulatory purposes">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Jurisdictions that allow the use of external ratings for regulatory purposes</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0135">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">assuming daily mark-to-market, daily remargining and a 10-business day holding period</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0136">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In jurisdictions that do not allow the use of external ratings for regulatory purposes, the following
supervisory haircuts (assuming daily mark-to-market, daily remargining and a 10-business day holding
period), expressed as percentages, must be used to determine the haircuts appropriate to the collateral
(Hc) and to the exposure (He):
73 Includes: PSEs that are treated as sovereigns by the national supervisor, as well as multilateral development banks receiving a
0% risk weight.</data>
