    <node id="OBL-0179">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Where the credit protection is denominated in a currency different from that in which the
exposure is denominated – ie there is a currency mismatch – the amount of the exposure deemed to be
protected must be reduced by the application of a haircut H FX, ie
( )
G =G⋅ 1−H
A FX
where:
G = nominal amount of the credit protection
H = haircut appropriate for currency mismatch between the credit protection and underlying
FX
obligation.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">Reduce the amount of the exposure deemed to be protected by applying a haircut H FX when there is a currency mismatch</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Institutions applying credit risk mitigation">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Institutions applying credit risk mitigation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0179">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
