    <node id="COND:OBL-0181">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to use the IRB approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0182">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Under the IRB approach, banks must categorise banking-book exposures into broad classes of
assets with different underlying risk characteristics, subject to the definitions set out below.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">categorise banking-book exposures into broad classes of assets with different underlying risk characteristics</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0182">
