    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0182">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">subject to the definitions set out below</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0183">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">While it is not the intention of the Committee to require banks to change the way in which they
manage their business and risks, banks are required to apply the appropriate treatment to each exposure
for the purposes of deriving their minimum capital requirement.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">apply the appropriate treatment to each exposure for the purposes of deriving their minimum capital requirement</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0183">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for the purposes of deriving their minimum capital requirement</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0183">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">while it is not the intention of the Committee to require banks to change the way in which they manage their business and risks</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0184">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must demonstrate to supervisors
that their methodology for assigning exposures to different classes is appropriate and consistent over
time.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">demonstrate to supervisors that their methodology for assigning exposures to different classes is appropriate and consistent over time</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0185">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In general, a corporate exposure is defined as a debt obligation of a corporation, partnership, or
proprietorship.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:corporate exposure">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">corporate exposure</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0186">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The borrowing entity has little or no other material assets or activities, and therefore little or no
independent capacity to repay the obligation, apart from the income that it receives from the
asset(s) being financed;</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0186">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">little or no other material assets or activities, and therefore little or no independent capacity to repay the obligation, apart from the income that it receives from the asset(s) being financed</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0187">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The terms of the obligation give the lender a substantial degree of control over the asset(s) and
the income that it generates;</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">have a substantial degree of control over the asset(s) and the income that it generates</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0187">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">the terms of the obligation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0188">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">and
• As a result of the preceding factors, the primary source of repayment of the obligation is the
income generated by the asset(s), rather than the independent capacity of a broader commercial
