    <node id="OBL-0194">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Within the retail asset class category, banks are required to identify separately three sub-classes
of exposures: (a) residential mortgage loans, as defined above, (b) qualifying revolving retail exposures, as
defined in the following paragraph, and (c) all other retail exposures.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">identify separately three sub-classes of exposures within the retail asset class category</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0194">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">within the retail asset class category</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0195">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">All of the following criteria must be satisfied for a sub-portfolio to be treated as a qualifying
revolving retail exposure (QRRE).</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">be treated as a qualifying revolving retail exposure (QRRE)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:sub-portfolio">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
