    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0195">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">all of the following criteria must be satisfied</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0196">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">These criteria must be applied at a sub-portfolio level consistent with the
bank’s segmentation of its retail activities generally.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">apply these criteria at a sub-portfolio level</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0196">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">consistent with the bank’s segmentation of its retail activities generally</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0197">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">(d) Because the asset correlation assumptions for the QRRE risk-weight function are markedly below
those for the other retail risk-weight function at low PD values, banks must demonstrate that the
use of the QRRE risk-weight function is constrained to portfolios that have exhibited low volatility
of loss rates, relative to their average level of loss rates, especially within the low PD bands.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">demonstrate that the use of the QRRE risk-weight function is constrained to portfolios that have exhibited low volatility of loss rates, relative to their average level of loss rates, especially within the low PD bands</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0197">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">because the asset correlation assumptions for the QRRE risk-weight function are markedly below those for the other retail risk-weight function at low PD values</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0198">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">(e) Data on loss rates for the sub-portfolio must be retained in order to allow analysis of the volatility
of loss rates.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">must be retained</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Data on loss rates for the sub-portfolio">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Data on loss rates for the sub-portfolio</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0198">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in order to allow analysis of the volatility of loss rates</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0199">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Basel III: Finalising post-crisis reforms 57
(f) The supervisor must concur that treatment as a qualifying revolving retail exposure is consistent
with the underlying risk characteristics of the sub-portfolio.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">concur that treatment as a qualifying revolving retail exposure is consistent with the underlying risk characteristics of the sub-portfolio</data>
    </node>
