    <node id="OBL-0203">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">(As such, intercompany accounts receivable and receivables subject to contra-accounts between
firms that buy and sell to each other are ineligible.5)
• The purchasing bank has a claim on all proceeds from the pool of receivables or a pro-rata
interest in the proceeds.6
• National supervisors must also establish concentration limits above which capital charges must
be calculated using the minimum requirements for the bottom-up approach for corporate
exposures.</data>
      <data key="d4">Preamble</data>
      <data key="d5">establish concentration limits above which capital charges must be calculated using the minimum requirements for the bottom-up approach for corporate exposures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0204">
