    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0258">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Whether adjustments are done through
PD or LGD, they must be done in a consistent manner for a given guarantee or credit derivative type.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">Adjust through PD or LGD in a consistent manner</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0258">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">For a given guarantee or credit derivative type</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0259">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In
case the bank applies the standardised approach to direct exposures to the guarantor it must assign the
standardised approach risk weight to the covered portion of the exposure.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must assign the standardised approach risk weight to the covered portion of the exposure</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0259">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in case the bank applies the standardised approach to direct exposures to the guarantor</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0260">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Consistent with the requirements outlined above for corporate and bank exposures, banks must
not include the effect of double default in such adjustments.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must not include the effect of double default in such adjustments</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0260">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">consistent with the requirements outlined above for corporate and bank exposures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0261">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The adjusted risk weight must not be less
than that of a comparable direct exposure to the protection provider.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must not be less than that of a comparable direct exposure to the protection provider</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The adjusted risk weight">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The adjusted risk weight</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0262">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks
must use their own estimates of EAD for undrawn revolving commitments to extend credit, purchase assets
or issue credit substitutes provided the exposure is not subject to a CCF of 100% in the standardised
approach (see paragraph 79 of the standardised approach) and the minimum requirements in paragraphs
241 to 251 are satisfied.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use their own estimates of EAD for undrawn revolving commitments to extend credit, purchase assets or issue credit substitutes</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0262">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">the exposure is not subject to a CCF of 100% in the standardised approach and the minimum requirements in paragraphs 241 to 251 are satisfied</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0262">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">exposures subject to a CCF of 100% in the standardised approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0263">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Foundation approach CCFs must be used for all other off-balance sheet items (for
example, undrawn non-revolving commitments), and must be used where the minimum requirements for
own estimates of EAD are not met.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">Use CCFs for all other off-balance sheet items and where minimum requirements for own estimates of EAD are not met</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Banks using the foundation approach">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
