      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">For off-balance sheet items such as undrawn non-revolving commitments, or when minimum requirements for own estimates of EAD are not met</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0264">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For retail exposures with uncertain future drawdown such as credit cards, banks must take into
account their history and/or expectation of additional drawings prior to default in their overall calibration
76 Basel III: Finalising post-crisis reforms
of loss estimates.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">take into account their history and/or expectation of additional drawings prior to default in their overall calibration of loss estimates</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0264">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for retail exposures with uncertain future drawdown such as credit cards</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0265">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In particular, where a bank does not reflect conversion factors for undrawn lines in its
EAD estimates, it must reflect in its LGD estimates the likelihood of additional drawings prior to default.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">reflect in its LGD estimates the likelihood of additional drawings prior to default</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0265">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where a bank does not reflect conversion factors for undrawn lines in its EAD estimates</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0266">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Conversely, if the bank does not incorporate the possibility of additional drawings in its LGD estimates, it
must do so in its EAD estimates.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must incorporate the possibility of additional drawings in its EAD estimates</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0266">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if the bank does not incorporate the possibility of additional drawings in its LGD estimates</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0267">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">When only the drawn balances of revolving retail facilities have been securitised, banks must
ensure that they continue to hold required capital against the undrawn balances associated with the
securitised exposures using the IRB approach to credit risk for commitments.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure that they continue to hold required capital against the undrawn balances associated with the securitised exposures using the IRB approach to credit risk for commitments</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0267">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when only the drawn balances of revolving retail facilities have been securitised</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0268">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For purchased retail receivables, a bank must meet the risk quantification standards for retail
exposures but can utilise external and internal reference data to estimate the PDs and LGDs.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must meet the risk quantification standards for retail exposures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0268">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for purchased retail receivables</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0268">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">can utilise external and internal reference data to estimate the PDs and LGDs</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0269">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The estimates
for PD and LGD (or EL) must be calculated for the receivables on a stand-alone basis;</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be calculated for the receivables on a stand-alone basis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The estimates for PD and LGD (or EL)">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The estimates for PD and LGD (or EL)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0270">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The estimated EL must be calculated for the receivables on a stand-alone basis;</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be calculated for the receivables on a stand-alone basis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The estimated EL">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The estimated EL</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0271">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In either case, it is important
to recognise that the LGD used for the IRB capital calculation for purchased receivables cannot be less
than the long-run default-weighted average loss rate given default and must be consistent with the
concepts defined in paragraph 235.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure the LGD used for IRB capital calculation is not less than the long-run default-weighted average loss rate given default and is consistent with the concepts in paragraph 235</data>
    </node>
