      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">LGD cannot be less than the long-run default-weighted average loss rate given default</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0272">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">This same value of M will also be used for undrawn amounts under a
committed purchase facility provided the facility contains effective covenants, early amortisation triggers,
or other features that protect the purchasing bank against a significant deterioration in the quality of the
future receivables it is required to purchase over the facility’s term.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use the same value of M for undrawn amounts under a committed purchase facility</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:purchasing bank">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">purchasing bank</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0272">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">the facility contains effective covenants, early amortisation triggers, or other features that protect the purchasing bank against a significant deterioration in the quality of the future receivables it is required to purchase over the facility’s term</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0273">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Dilution refers to the possibility that the receivable amount is reduced through cash or non-cash
credits to the receivable’s obligor.20 For both corporate and retail receivables, unless the bank can
demonstrate to its supervisor that the dilution risk for the purchasing bank is immaterial, the treatment of
dilution risk must be the following: at the level of either the pool as a whole (top-down approach) or the
individual receivables making up the pool (bottom-up approach), the purchasing bank will estimate the
one-year EL for dilution risk, also expressed in percentage of the receivables amount.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">estimate the one-year EL for dilution risk, also expressed in percentage of the receivables amount</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0273">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">unless the bank can demonstrate to its supervisor that the dilution risk for the purchasing bank is immaterial</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0273">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">one-year</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0273">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">if the bank can demonstrate to its supervisor that the dilution risk is immaterial</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0274">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">As with the treatments of default risk, this estimate must be
computed on a stand-alone basis;</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">compute the estimate on a stand-alone basis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0274">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">as with the treatments of default risk</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0275">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For the purpose of calculating risk weights for dilution risk, the corporate
risk-weight function must be used with the following settings: the PD must be set equal to the estimated
EL, and the LGD must be set at 100%.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be used with the PD set equal to the estimated EL and the LGD set at 100% for calculating risk weights for dilution risk</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the corporate risk-weight function">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the corporate risk-weight function</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0275">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for the purpose of calculating risk weights for dilution risk</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0276">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">To the extent that a portion of such a purchase price discount may be
refunded to the seller based on the performance of the receivables, the purchaser may recognise this
refundable amount as first-loss protection and hence treat this exposure under the securitisation
framework, while the seller providing such a refundable purchase price discount must treat the refundable
amount as a first-loss position under the securitisation framework.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">recognise the refundable amount as first-loss protection and treat this exposure under the securitisation framework</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:purchaser">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">purchaser</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0276">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to the extent that a portion of the purchase price discount may be refunded to the seller based on the performance of the receivables</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0277">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Basel III: Finalising post-crisis reforms 79
risk, banks using the Securitisation Internal Ratings-Based Approach (SEC-IRBA) that are able to calculate
an exposure-weighted LGD must do so as defined in paragraph 60 of the securitisation framework.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">calculate an exposure-weighted LGD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:banks using the Securitisation Internal Ratings-Based Approach (SEC-IRBA)">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">banks using the Securitisation Internal Ratings-Based Approach (SEC-IRBA)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0277">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">that are able to calculate an exposure-weighted LGD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0278">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Section G discusses the method by which the difference between provisions (eg specific
provisions, portfolio-specific general provisions such as country risk provisions or general provisions) and
expected losses may be included in or must be deducted from regulatory capital, as outlined in the
definition of capital section of the Basel III framework (June 2011).</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">include or deduct the difference between provisions and expected losses from regulatory capital</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0278">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">as outlined in the definition of capital section of the Basel III framework (June 2011)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0279">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A bank must sum the EL amount (defined as EL multiplied by EAD) associated with its exposures
to which the IRB approach is applied (excluding the EL amount associated with securitisation exposures)
to obtain a total EL amount.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">sum the EL amount (defined as EL multiplied by EAD) associated with its exposures to which the IRB approach is applied to obtain a total EL amount</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0279">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">exposures to which the IRB approach is applied</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0279">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">excluding the EL amount associated with securitisation exposures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0280">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must calculate EL as PD x LGD for corporate, bank, and retail exposures not in default.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">calculate EL as PD x LGD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0280">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for corporate, bank, and retail exposures not in default</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0281">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For
corporate, bank, and retail exposures that are in default, banks must use their best estimate of expected
loss as defined in paragraph 238 for exposures subject to the advanced approach and for exposures
subject to the foundation approach banks must use the supervisory LGD.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use their best estimate of expected loss as defined in paragraph 238 for exposures subject to the advanced approach and use the supervisory LGD for exposures subject to the foundation approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0281">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for corporate, bank, and retail exposures that are in default</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0282">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Specific provisions set aside against securitisation exposures
must not be included in total eligible provisions.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must not be included in total eligible provisions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Specific provisions set aside against securitisation exposures">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Specific provisions set aside against securitisation exposures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0283">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks using the standardised approach for a portion of their credit risk exposures (see paragraphs
44 to 48), must determine the portion of general provisions attributed to the standardised or IRB treatment
of provisions according to the methods outlined in paragraphs 149 and 150.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">determine the portion of general provisions attributed to the standardised or IRB treatment of provisions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Banks using the standardised approach for a portion of their credit risk exposures">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Banks using the standardised approach for a portion of their credit risk exposures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0283">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">using the standardised approach for a portion of their credit risk exposures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0284">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">As specified in paragraphs 61 and 73 of the Basel III framework (June 2011), banks using the IRB
approach must compare the total amount of total eligible provisions (as defined in paragraph 147) with
the total EL amount as calculated within the IRB approach (as defined in paragraph 142).</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">compare the total amount of total eligible provisions with the total EL amount as calculated within the IRB approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:banks using the IRB approach">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">banks using the IRB approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0284">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">as specified in paragraphs 61 and 73 of the Basel III framework (June 2011)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0285">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Where the calculated EL amount is lower than the total eligible provisions of the bank, its
supervisors must consider whether the EL fully reflects the conditions in the market in which it operates
before allowing the difference to be included in Tier 2 capital.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">consider whether the EL fully reflects the conditions in the market in which the bank operates</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0285">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where the calculated EL amount is lower than the total eligible provisions of the bank</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0285">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">before allowing the difference to be included in Tier 2 capital</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0286">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">To be eligible for the IRB approach a bank must demonstrate to its supervisor that it meets certain
minimum requirements at the outset and on an ongoing basis.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">demonstrate to its supervisor that it meets certain minimum requirements</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0286">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to be eligible for the IRB approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0286">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">at the outset and on an ongoing basis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0287">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Many of these requirements are in the
form of objectives that a qualifying bank’s risk rating systems must fulfil.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">fulfil objectives for risk rating systems</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:qualifying bank">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">qualifying bank</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0287">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">requirements in the form of objectives</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0288">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Furthermore, the systems and processes must be consistent with internal use of these estimates.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be consistent with internal use of these estimates</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the systems and processes">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the systems and processes</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0289">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Each
supervisor will develop detailed review procedures to ensure that banks’ systems and controls are
adequate to serve as the basis for the IRB approach.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">develop detailed review procedures to ensure that banks’ systems and controls are adequate to serve as the basis for the IRB approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Each supervisor">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Each supervisor</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0290">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Generally, all IRB banks must produce their own estimates of PD22
and must adhere to the overall requirements for rating system design, operations, controls, and corporate
governance, as well as the requisite requirements for estimation and validation of PD measures.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">produce their own estimates of PD22 and adhere to the overall requirements for rating system design, operations, controls, and corporate governance, as well as the requisite requirements for estimation and validation of PD measures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:IRB banks">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">IRB banks</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0290">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">Generally</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0291">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks
wishing to use their own estimates of LGD and EAD must also meet the incremental minimum
requirements for these risk factors included in paragraphs 235 to 263.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">meet the incremental minimum requirements for LGD and EAD estimates</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0291">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">wishing to use their own estimates of LGD and EAD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0292">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">To be eligible for an IRB approach, a bank must demonstrate to its supervisor that it meets the
IRB requirements in this document, at the outset and on an ongoing basis.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">demonstrate to its supervisor that it meets the IRB requirements in this document</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0292">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to be eligible for an IRB approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0292">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">at the outset and on an ongoing basis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0293">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks’ overall credit risk
management practices must also be consistent with the evolving sound practice guidelines issued by the
Committee and national supervisors.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure overall credit risk management practices are consistent with evolving sound practice guidelines</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0293">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">issued by the Committee and national supervisors</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0294">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Where this is the case, the bank must produce a plan for a timely return to compliance, and
seek approval from its supervisor, or the bank must demonstrate that the effect of such non-compliance
is immaterial in terms of the risk posed to the institution.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">produce a plan for a timely return to compliance and seek approval from its supervisor, or demonstrate that the effect of such non-compliance is immaterial in terms of the risk posed to the institution</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0294">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where this is the case</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0294">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">timely</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0295">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">If a bank chooses to use multiple systems, the rationale for assigning a borrower to
a rating system must be documented and applied in a manner that best reflects the level of risk of the
borrower.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">document and apply the rationale for assigning a borrower to a rating system in a manner that best reflects the level of risk of the borrower</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0295">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if the bank chooses to use multiple systems</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0296">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must not allocate borrowers across rating systems inappropriately to minimise regulatory
capital requirements (ie cherry-picking by choice of rating system).</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must not allocate borrowers across rating systems inappropriately to minimise regulatory capital requirements</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0296">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to minimise regulatory capital requirements</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0297">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must demonstrate that each
system used for IRB purposes is in compliance with the minimum requirements at the outset and on an
ongoing basis.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">demonstrate that each system used for IRB purposes is in compliance with the minimum requirements</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0297">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">at the outset and on an ongoing basis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0298">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A qualifying IRB rating system must have two separate and distinct dimensions: (i) the risk of
borrower default;</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have two separate and distinct dimensions: (i) the risk of borrower default</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:A qualifying IRB rating system">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">A qualifying IRB rating system</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0299">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The first dimension must be oriented to the risk of borrower default.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be oriented to the risk of borrower default</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The first dimension">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The first dimension</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0300">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Separate exposures to the
same borrower must be assigned to the same borrower grade, irrespective of any differences in the nature
of each specific transaction.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be assigned to the same borrower grade</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Separate exposures to the same borrower">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Separate exposures to the same borrower</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0300">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">irrespective of any differences in the nature of each specific transaction</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0301">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A bank must articulate in its credit policy the relationship between borrower grades
in terms of the level of risk each grade implies.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must articulate in its credit policy the relationship between borrower grades in terms of the level of risk each grade implies</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0302">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Perceived and measured risk must increase as credit quality
declines from one grade to the next.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">increase as credit quality declines from one grade to the next</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Perceived and measured risk">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Perceived and measured risk</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0302">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">as credit quality declines from one grade to the next</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0303">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The policy must articulate the risk of each grade in terms of both a
description of the probability of default risk typical for borrowers assigned the grade and the criteria used
to distinguish that level of credit risk.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">articulate the risk of each grade in terms of both a description of the probability of default risk typical for borrowers assigned the grade and the criteria used to distinguish that level of credit risk</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The policy">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The policy</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0304">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The second dimension must reflect transaction-specific factors, such as collateral, seniority,
product type, etc.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must reflect transaction-specific factors</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The second dimension">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The second dimension</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0304">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">such as collateral, seniority, product type, etc.</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0305">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Where a rating dimension reflects EL and does not separately quantify LGD, the supervisory estimates of
LGD must be used.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use supervisory estimates of LGD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:rating dimension that reflects EL and does not separately quantify LGD">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">rating dimension that reflects EL and does not separately quantify LGD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0305">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where a rating dimension reflects EL and does not separately quantify LGD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0306">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For banks using the advanced approach, facility ratings must reflect exclusively LGD.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">facility ratings must reflect exclusively LGD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:banks using the advanced approach">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">banks using the advanced approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0307">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Rating systems for retail exposures must be oriented to both borrower and transaction risk, and
must capture all relevant borrower and transaction characteristics.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be oriented to both borrower and transaction risk, and must capture all relevant borrower and transaction characteristics</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Rating systems for retail exposures">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Rating systems for retail exposures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0308">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must assign each exposure that
falls within the definition of retail for IRB purposes into a particular pool.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">assign each exposure that falls within the definition of retail for IRB purposes into a particular pool</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0308">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">exposure falls within the definition of retail for IRB purposes</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0309">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must demonstrate that this
process provides for a meaningful differentiation of risk, provides for a grouping of sufficiently
homogenous exposures, and allows for accurate and consistent estimation of loss characteristics at pool
level.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">demonstrate that the process provides for a meaningful differentiation of risk, provides for a grouping of sufficiently homogenous exposures, and allows for accurate and consistent estimation of loss characteristics at pool level</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0310">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For each pool, banks must estimate PD, LGD, and EAD.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">estimate PD, LGD, and EAD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0310">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for each pool</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0311">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must explicitly
address cross-collateral provisions where present.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">explicitly address cross-collateral provisions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0311">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where present</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0312">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A bank must have a meaningful distribution of exposures across grades with no excessive
concentrations, on both its borrower-rating and its facility-rating scales.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have a meaningful distribution of exposures across grades with no excessive concentrations</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0312">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">on both its borrower-rating and its facility-rating scales</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0313">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">To meet this objective, a bank must have a minimum of seven borrower grades for non-defaulted
borrowers and one for those that have defaulted.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have a minimum of seven borrower grades for non-defaulted borrowers and one for those that have defaulted</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0313">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">7 borrower grades for non-defaulted borrowers, 1 for defaulted borrowers</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0314">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The grade definition must include
both a description of the degree of default risk typical for borrowers assigned the grade and the criteria
used to distinguish that level of credit risk.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">include both a description of the degree of default risk typical for borrowers assigned the grade and the criteria used to distinguish that level of credit risk</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The grade definition">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The grade definition</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0315">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks with loan portfolios concentrated in a particular market segment and range of default risk
must have enough grades within that range to avoid undue concentrations of borrowers in particular
grades.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must have enough grades within that range to avoid undue concentrations of borrowers in particular grades</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Banks with loan portfolios concentrated in a particular market segment and range of default risk">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Banks with loan portfolios concentrated in a particular market segment and range of default risk</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0315">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">loan portfolios concentrated in a particular market segment and range of default risk</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0316">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Significant concentrations within a single grade or grades must be supported by convincing
empirical evidence that the grade or grades cover reasonably narrow PD bands and that the default risk
posed by all borrowers in a grade fall within that band.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be supported by convincing empirical evidence that the grade or grades cover reasonably narrow PD bands and that the default risk posed by all borrowers in a grade fall within that band</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Significant concentrations within a single grade or grades">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Significant concentrations within a single grade or grades</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0317">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A bank must have a sufficient number of facility grades to avoid grouping facilities
with widely varying LGDs into a single grade.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have a sufficient number of facility grades</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0317">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to avoid grouping facilities with widely varying LGDs into a single grade</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0318">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The criteria used to define facility grades must be grounded
in empirical evidence.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ground the criteria used to define facility grades in empirical evidence</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The entity defining facility grades">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The entity defining facility grades</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0319">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks using the supervisory slotting criteria must have at least four grades for non-defaulted
borrowers, and one for defaulted borrowers.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have at least four grades for non-defaulted borrowers, and one for defaulted borrowers</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Banks using the supervisory slotting criteria">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Banks using the supervisory slotting criteria</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0319">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">four grades for non-defaulted borrowers, one for defaulted borrowers</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0320">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For each pool identified, the bank must be able to provide quantitative measures of loss
characteristics (PD, LGD, and EAD) for that pool.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">provide quantitative measures of loss characteristics (PD, LGD, and EAD) for that pool</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0320">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for each pool identified</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0321">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The level of differentiation for IRB purposes must ensure
that the number of exposures in a given pool is sufficient so as to allow for meaningful quantification and
validation of the loss characteristics at the pool level.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure that the number of exposures in a given pool is sufficient to allow for meaningful quantification and validation of the loss characteristics at the pool level</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Institutions using IRB approach">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Institutions using IRB approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0321">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for IRB purposes</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0321">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">sufficient number of exposures to allow meaningful quantification and validation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0322">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">There must be a meaningful distribution of borrowers
and exposures across pools.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure a meaningful distribution of borrowers and exposures across pools</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0323">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A single pool must not include an undue concentration of the bank’s total
retail exposure.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must not include an undue concentration of the bank’s total retail exposure</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:A single pool">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">A single pool</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0324">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A bank must have specific rating definitions, processes and criteria for assigning exposures to
grades within a rating system.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have specific rating definitions, processes and criteria for assigning exposures to grades within a rating system</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0325">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The rating definitions and criteria must be both plausible and intuitive and
must result in a meaningful differentiation of risk.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be both plausible and intuitive and must result in a meaningful differentiation of risk</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The rating definitions and criteria">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The rating definitions and criteria</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0326">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The grade descriptions and criteria must be sufficiently detailed to allow those charged with
assigning ratings to consistently assign the same grade to borrowers or facilities posing similar
risk.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">Consistently assign the same grade to borrowers or facilities posing similar risk</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Those charged with assigning ratings">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Those charged with assigning ratings</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0326">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">Grade descriptions and criteria must be sufficiently detailed</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0327">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">If rating criteria and procedures differ for different types of borrowers or facilities, the bank must
Basel III: Finalising post-crisis reforms 85
monitor for possible inconsistency, and must alter rating criteria to improve consistency when
appropriate.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">monitor for possible inconsistency and alter rating criteria to improve consistency</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0327">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if rating criteria and procedures differ for different types of borrowers or facilities</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0328">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• Written rating definitions must be clear and detailed enough to allow third parties to understand
the assignment of ratings, such as internal audit or an equally independent function and
supervisors, to replicate rating assignments and evaluate the appropriateness of the grade/pool
assignments.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">Ensure written rating definitions are clear and detailed enough to allow third parties to replicate rating assignments and evaluate the appropriateness of grade/pool assignments</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Rating issuer">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Rating issuer</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0328">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">When assigning ratings</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0329">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The criteria must also be consistent with the bank’s internal lending standards and its policies for
handling troubled borrowers and facilities.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be consistent with the bank’s internal lending standards and its policies for handling troubled borrowers and facilities</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The criteria">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The criteria</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0330">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">To ensure that banks are consistently taking into account available information, they must use all
relevant and material information in assigning ratings to borrowers and facilities.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use all relevant and material information in assigning ratings to borrowers and facilities</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0330">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to ensure that banks are consistently taking into account available information</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0331">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Information must be
current.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">Information must be current</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0332">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The less information a bank has, the more conservative must be its assignments of exposures to
borrower and facility grades or pools.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">assign exposures to borrower and facility grades or pools conservatively</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0332">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">the less information the bank has</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0333">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">however, the bank must ensure that it considers other relevant information.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure that it considers other relevant information</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0334">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks using the supervisory slotting criteria must assign exposures to their internal rating grades
based on their own criteria, systems and processes, subject to compliance with the requisite minimum
requirements.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">assign exposures to their internal rating grades based on their own criteria, systems and processes</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0334">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">subject to compliance with the requisite minimum requirements</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0335">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must then map these internal rating grades into the five supervisory rating categories.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">map these internal rating grades into the five supervisory rating categories</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0335">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0336">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">however, banks must
demonstrate that their mapping process has resulted in an alignment of grades which is consistent with
the preponderance of the characteristics in the respective supervisory category.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">demonstrate that their mapping process has resulted in an alignment of grades which is consistent with the preponderance of the characteristics in the respective supervisory category</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0337">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks should take special
care to ensure that any overrides of their internal criteria do not render the mapping process ineffective.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">take special care to ensure that any overrides of their internal criteria do not render the mapping process ineffective</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0337">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when overriding internal criteria</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0338">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A borrower rating must represent the bank’s assessment of the borrower’s ability and willingness
to contractually perform despite adverse economic conditions or the occurrence of unexpected events.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">represent borrower rating as assessment of borrower’s ability and willingness to contractually perform</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0338">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">despite adverse economic conditions or the occurrence of unexpected events</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0339">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The range of economic conditions that are considered when making assessments must be consistent with
current conditions and those that are likely to occur over a business cycle within the respective
industry/geographic region.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure the range of economic conditions considered is consistent with current conditions and those likely to occur over a business cycle</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:entities making assessments">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">entities making assessments</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0339">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when making assessments</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0340">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">PD estimates for borrowers that are highly leveraged or for borrowers whose assets are
predominantly traded assets must reflect the performance of the underlying assets based on periods of
stressed volatilities.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">reflect the performance of the underlying assets based on periods of stressed volatilities</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:PD estimates for borrowers">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">PD estimates for borrowers</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0340">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">borrowers that are highly leveraged or borrowers whose assets are predominantly traded assets</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0341">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Given the difficulties in forecasting future events and the influence they will have on a particular
borrower’s financial condition, a bank must take a conservative view of projected information.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">take a conservative view of projected information</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0341">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">given the difficulties in forecasting future events and the influence they will have on a particular borrower’s financial condition</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0342">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Furthermore, where limited data are available, a bank must adopt a conservative bias to its analysis.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">adopt a conservative bias to its analysis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0342">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where limited data are available</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0343">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Sufficient human judgement and human oversight is necessary to ensure that all relevant and material
information, including that which is outside the scope of the model, is also taken into consideration, and
that the model is used appropriately.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure sufficient human judgement and human oversight</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:users of the model">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">users of the model</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0343">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to consider all relevant and material information, including information outside the scope of the model, and to ensure the model is used appropriately</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0344">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The
variables that are input to the model must form a reasonable set of predictors.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must form a reasonable set of predictors</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The variables that are input to the model">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The variables that are input to the model</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0345">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The model must
be accurate on average across the range of borrowers or facilities to which the bank is exposed
and there must be no known material biases.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">be accurate on average across the range of borrowers or facilities to which the bank is exposed and have no known material biases</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the model">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the model</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0345">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">across the range of borrowers or facilities to which the bank is exposed</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0346">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The bank must have in place a process for vetting data inputs into a statistical default or loss
prediction model which includes an assessment of the accuracy, completeness and
appropriateness of the data specific to the assignment of an approved rating.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have in place a process for vetting data inputs into a statistical default or loss prediction model which includes an assessment of the accuracy, completeness and appropriateness of the data specific to the assignment of an approved rating</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0346">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">specific to the assignment of an approved rating</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0347">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The bank must demonstrate that the data used to build the model are representative of the
population of the bank’s actual borrowers or facilities.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">demonstrate that the data used to build the model are representative of the population of the bank’s actual borrowers or facilities</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0348">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• When combining model results with human judgement, the judgement must take into account
all relevant and material information not considered by the model.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must take into account all relevant and material information not considered by the model</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The judgement">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The judgement</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0348">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when combining model results with human judgement</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0349">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The bank must have written
guidance describing how human judgement and model results are to be combined.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must have written guidance describing how human judgement and model results are to be combined</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0350">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The bank must have procedures for human review of model-based rating assignments.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have procedures for human review of model-based rating assignments</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0351">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Such
procedures should focus on finding and limiting errors associated with known model weaknesses
and must also include credible ongoing efforts to improve the model’s performance.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">focus on finding and limiting errors associated with known model weaknesses and include credible ongoing efforts to improve the model’s performance</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Such procedures">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Such procedures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0352">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The bank must have a regular cycle of model validation that includes monitoring of model
performance and stability;</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have a regular cycle of model validation that includes monitoring of model performance and stability</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0353">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must document in writing their rating systems’ design and operational details.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">document in writing their rating systems’ design and operational details</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0354">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The
documentation must evidence banks’ compliance with the minimum standards, and must address topics
such as portfolio differentiation, rating criteria, responsibilities of parties that rate borrowers and facilities,
definition of what constitutes a rating exception, parties that have authority to approve exceptions,
frequency of rating reviews, and management oversight of the rating process.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">evidence compliance with the minimum standards in documentation and address specified topics related to the rating process</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0354">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when providing documentation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0355">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A bank must document the
rationale for its choice of internal rating criteria and must be able to provide analyses demonstrating that
rating criteria and procedures are likely to result in ratings that meaningfully differentiate risk.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must document the rationale for its choice of internal rating criteria and must be able to provide analyses demonstrating that rating criteria and procedures are likely to result in ratings that meaningfully differentiate risk</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0356">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Rating
criteria and procedures must be periodically reviewed to determine whether they remain fully applicable
to the current portfolio and to external conditions.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be periodically reviewed</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Rating criteria and procedures">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Rating criteria and procedures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0356">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to determine whether they remain fully applicable to the current portfolio and to external conditions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0357">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In addition, a bank must document a history of major
changes in the risk rating process, and such documentation must support identification of changes made
to the risk rating process subsequent to the last supervisory review.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">document a history of major changes in the risk rating process</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0357">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to support identification of changes made to the risk rating process subsequent to the last supervisory review</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0358">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The organisation of rating assignment,
including the internal control structure, must also be documented.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">document the organisation of rating assignment, including the internal control structure</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The organisation">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The organisation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0359">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must document the specific definitions of default and loss used internally and demonstrate
consistency with the reference definitions set out in paragraphs 220 to 228.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">document the specific definitions of default and loss used internally and demonstrate consistency with the reference definitions set out in paragraphs 220 to 228</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0359">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">internal use of definitions of default and loss</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0360">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">If the bank employs statistical models in the rating process, the bank must document their
methodologies.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must document their methodologies</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0360">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if the bank employs statistical models in the rating process</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0361">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">This material must:
• Provide a detailed outline of the theory, assumptions and/or mathematical and empirical basis of
the assignment of estimates to grades, individual obligors, exposures, or pools, and the data
source(s) used to estimate the model;</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">Provide a detailed outline of the theory, assumptions and/or mathematical and empirical basis of the assignment of estimates to grades, individual obligors, exposures, or pools, and the data source(s) used to estimate the model</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:This material">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">This material</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0362">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For corporate, and bank exposures, each borrower and all recognised guarantors must be
assigned a rating and each exposure must be associated with a facility rating as part of the loan approval
process.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">assign a rating to each borrower and all recognised guarantors, and associate each exposure with a facility rating</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:financial institutions">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">financial institutions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0362">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for corporate and bank exposures during the loan approval process</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0363">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Similarly, for retail, each exposure must be assigned to a pool as part of the loan approval process.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">assign each exposure to a pool</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:retail">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">retail</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0363">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">as part of the loan approval process</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0364">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Each separate legal entity to which the bank is exposed must be separately rated.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">separately rate each separate legal entity to which it is exposed</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0365">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A bank must
have policies acceptable to its supervisor regarding the treatment of individual entities in a connected
group including circumstances under which the same rating may or may not be assigned to some or all
related entities.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have policies acceptable to its supervisor regarding the treatment of individual entities in a connected group including circumstances under which the same rating may or may not be assigned to some or all related entities</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0366">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Those policies must include a process for the identification of specific wrong way risk for
each legal entity to which the bank is exposed.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">include a process for the identification of specific wrong way risk</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Those policies">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Those policies</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0366">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for each legal entity to which the bank is exposed</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0367">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Rating assignments and periodic rating reviews must be completed or approved by a party that
does not directly stand to benefit from the extension of credit.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">complete or approve rating assignments and periodic rating reviews</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:party">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">party</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0367">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when rating assignments and periodic rating reviews are conducted</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0368">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">These
operational processes must be documented in the bank’s procedures and incorporated into bank policies.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">document operational processes in procedures and incorporate into policies</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0369">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Credit policies and underwriting procedures must reinforce and foster the independence of the rating
process.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">reinforce and foster the independence of the rating process</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Credit policies and underwriting procedures">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Credit policies and underwriting procedures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0370">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Borrowers and facilities must have their ratings refreshed at least on an annual basis.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have their ratings refreshed</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Borrowers and facilities">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Borrowers and facilities</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0370">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">at least on an annual basis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0371">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Certain
credits, especially higher risk borrowers or problem exposures, must be subject to more frequent review.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be subject to more frequent review</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:certain credits, especially higher risk borrowers or problem exposures">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">certain credits, especially higher risk borrowers or problem exposures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0371">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if they are higher risk borrowers or problem exposures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0372">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In addition, banks must initiate a new rating if material information on the borrower or facility comes to
light.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">initiate a new rating</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0372">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">material information on the borrower or facility comes to light</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0373">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The bank must have an effective process to obtain and update relevant and material information
on the borrower’s financial condition, and on facility characteristics that affect LGDs and EADs (such as the
condition of collateral).</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have an effective process to obtain and update relevant and material information on the borrower’s financial condition, and on facility characteristics that affect LGDs and EADs</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0373">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">information related to borrower’s financial condition and facility characteristics affecting LGDs and EADs, such as the condition of collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0374">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A bank must review the loss characteristics and delinquency status of each identified risk pool on
at least an annual basis.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">review the loss characteristics and delinquency status of each identified risk pool</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0374">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">each identified risk pool</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0374">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">on at least an annual basis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0375">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">It must also review the status of individual borrowers within each pool as a means
of ensuring that exposures continue to be assigned to the correct pool.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">review the status of individual borrowers within each pool</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:It">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">It</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0375">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">as a means of ensuring that exposures continue to be assigned to the correct pool</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0376">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For rating assignments based on expert judgement, banks must clearly articulate the situations
in which bank officers may override the outputs of the rating process, including how and to what extent
such overrides can be used and by whom.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">clearly articulate the situations in which bank officers may override the outputs of the rating process, including how and to what extent such overrides can be used and by whom</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0376">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for rating assignments based on expert judgement</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0377">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For model-based ratings, the bank must have guidelines and
processes for monitoring cases where human judgement has overridden the model’s rating, variables were
excluded or inputs were altered.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have guidelines and processes for monitoring cases where human judgement has overridden the model’s rating, variables were excluded or inputs were altered</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0377">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for model-based ratings</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0378">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">These guidelines must include identifying personnel that are responsible
for approving these overrides.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">include identifying personnel that are responsible for approving these overrides</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:These guidelines">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">These guidelines</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0379">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must identify overrides and separately track their performance.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">identify overrides and separately track their performance</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0380">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A bank must collect and store data on key borrower and facility characteristics to provide effective
support to its internal credit risk measurement and management process, to enable the bank to meet the
other requirements in this document, and to serve as a basis for supervisory reporting.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">collect and store data on key borrower and facility characteristics</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0380">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to provide effective support to its internal credit risk measurement and management process, to enable the bank to meet the other requirements in this document, and to serve as a basis for supervisory reporting</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0381">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Furthermore, banks must collect and retain data on aspects of their internal ratings as
required under Pillar 3 of this Framework.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">collect and retain data on aspects of their internal ratings</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0381">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">as required under Pillar 3 of this Framework</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0382">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must maintain rating histories on borrowers and recognised guarantors, including the
rating since the borrower/guarantor was assigned an internal grade, the dates the ratings were assigned,
the methodology and key data used to derive the rating and the person/model responsible.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">maintain rating histories on borrowers and recognised guarantors</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0382">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">including the rating since the borrower/guarantor was assigned an internal grade, the dates the ratings were assigned, the methodology and key data used to derive the rating and the person/model responsible</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0383">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The identity
of borrowers and facilities that default, and the timing and circumstances of such defaults, must be
retained.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">retain the identity of borrowers and facilities that default, and the timing and circumstances of such defaults</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:regulated entity">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">regulated entity</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0383">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when defaults occur</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0384">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must also retain data on the PDs and realised default rates associated with rating grades
and ratings migration in order to track the predictive power of the borrower rating system.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">retain data on the PDs and realised default rates associated with rating grades and ratings migration</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0384">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in order to track the predictive power of the borrower rating system</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0385">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks using the advanced IRB approach must also collect and store a complete history of data
on the LGD and EAD estimates associated with each facility and the key data used to derive the estimate
and the person/model responsible.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">collect and store a complete history of data on the LGD and EAD estimates associated with each facility and the key data used to derive the estimate and the person/model responsible</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Banks using the advanced IRB approach">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Banks using the advanced IRB approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0386">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must also collect data on the estimated and realised LGDs and
EADs associated with each defaulted facility.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">collect data on the estimated and realised LGDs and EADs associated with each defaulted facility</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0386">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">associated with each defaulted facility</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0387">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks that reflect the credit risk mitigating effects of
guarantees/credit derivatives through LGD must retain data on the LGD of the facility before and after
evaluation of the effects of the guarantee/credit derivative.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">retain data on the LGD of the facility before and after evaluation of the effects of the guarantee/credit derivative</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0387">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">that reflect the credit risk mitigating effects of guarantees/credit derivatives through LGD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0388">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Information about the components of loss or
recovery for each defaulted exposure must be retained, such as amounts recovered, source of recovery
(eg collateral, liquidation proceeds and guarantees), time period required for recovery, and administrative
costs.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">retain information about the components of loss or recovery for each defaulted exposure</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0388">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for each defaulted exposure</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0389">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must retain data used in the process of allocating exposures to pools, including data on
borrower and transaction risk characteristics used either directly or through use of a model, as well as data
on delinquency.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">retain data used in the process of allocating exposures to pools, including data on borrower and transaction risk characteristics used either directly or through use of a model, as well as data on delinquency</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0390">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must also retain data on the estimated PDs, LGDs and EADs, associated with pools
Basel III: Finalising post-crisis reforms 89
of exposures.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">retain data on the estimated PDs, LGDs and EADs associated with pools of exposures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0391">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For defaulted exposures, banks must retain the data on the pools to which the exposure was
assigned over the year prior to default and the realised outcomes on LGD and EAD.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">retain the data on the pools to which the exposure was assigned over the year prior to default and the realised outcomes on LGD and EAD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0391">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for defaulted exposures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0392">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">An IRB bank must have in place sound stress testing processes for use in the assessment of capital
adequacy.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have in place sound stress testing processes for use in the assessment of capital adequacy</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:An IRB bank">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">An IRB bank</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0393">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Stress testing must involve identifying possible events or future changes in economic conditions
that could have unfavourable effects on a bank’s credit exposures and assessment of the bank’s ability to
withstand such changes.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">identify possible events or future changes in economic conditions that could have unfavourable effects on credit exposures and assess ability to withstand such changes</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0393">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">during stress testing</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0394">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In addition to the more general tests described above, the bank must perform a credit risk stress
test to assess the effect of certain specific conditions on its IRB regulatory capital requirements.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">perform a credit risk stress test to assess the effect of certain specific conditions on its IRB regulatory capital requirements</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0394">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in addition to the more general tests described above</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0395">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The test to be employed
must be meaningful and reasonably conservative.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">employ a test that is meaningful and reasonably conservative</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0396">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Whatever method is used, the bank must include a consideration of the following sources of
information.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">include a consideration of the following sources of information</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0396">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">Whatever method is used</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0397">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">All material aspects of the rating and estimation processes must be approved by the bank’s board
of directors or a designated committee thereof and senior management.24 These parties must possess a
general understanding of the bank’s risk rating system and detailed comprehension of its associated
management reports.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">approve all material aspects of the rating and estimation processes</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:bank’s board of directors or a designated committee thereof and senior management">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">bank’s board of directors or a designated committee thereof and senior management</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0397">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">related to the bank’s risk rating system and its associated management reports</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0398">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Senior management must provide notice to the board of directors or a designated
committee thereof of material changes or exceptions from established policies that will materially impact
the operations of the bank’s rating system.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">provide notice to the board of directors or a designated committee thereof of material changes or exceptions from established policies</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Senior management">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Senior management</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0398">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">that will materially impact the operations of the bank’s rating system</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0399">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In some countries, the board has the main, if not exclusive, function of
supervising the executive body (senior management, general management) so as to ensure that the latter fulfils its tasks.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">supervising the executive body (senior management, general management)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:board">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">board</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0399">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in some countries</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0399">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">if not exclusive</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0400">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Senior management also must have a good understanding of the rating system’s design and
operation, and must approve material differences between established procedure and actual practice.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have a good understanding of the rating system’s design and operation, and must approve material differences between established procedure and actual practice</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0400">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">material differences between established procedure and actual practice</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0401">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Management must also ensure, on an ongoing basis, that the rating system is operating properly.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure that the rating system is operating properly</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Management">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Management</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0401">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">on an ongoing basis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0402">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Management and staff in the credit control function must meet regularly to discuss the performance of
the rating process, areas needing improvement, and the status of efforts to improve previously identified
deficiencies.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">meet regularly to discuss the performance of the rating process, areas needing improvement, and the status of efforts to improve previously identified deficiencies</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Management and staff in the credit control function">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Management and staff in the credit control function</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0403">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Internal ratings must be an essential part of the reporting to these parties.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">be an essential part of the reporting</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Internal ratings">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Internal ratings</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0403">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">reporting to these parties</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0404">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Reporting must include
risk profile by grade, migration across grades, estimation of the relevant parameters per grade, and
comparison of realised default rates (and LGDs and EADs for banks on advanced approaches) against
expectations.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">include risk profile by grade, migration across grades, estimation of the relevant parameters per grade, and comparison of realised default rates (and LGDs and EADs for banks on advanced approaches) against expectations</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Reporting entity">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Reporting entity</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0404">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for banks on advanced approaches, when reporting default rates, LGDs, and EADs</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0405">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must have independent credit risk control units that are responsible for the design or
selection, implementation and performance of their internal rating systems.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have independent credit risk control units responsible for the design or selection, implementation and performance of their internal rating systems</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0406">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The unit(s) must be
functionally independent from the personnel and management functions responsible for originating
exposures.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">be functionally independent from the personnel and management functions responsible for originating exposures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:unit(s)">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">unit(s)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0407">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Areas of responsibility must include:
• Testing and monitoring internal grades;</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">include testing and monitoring internal grades</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Areas of responsibility">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Areas of responsibility</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0408">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Changes to the rating
process, criteria or individual rating parameters must be documented and retained for supervisors
to review.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">document and retain changes to the rating process, criteria or individual rating parameters</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The entity responsible for the rating process">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The entity responsible for the rating process</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0408">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when changes are made to the rating process, criteria or individual rating parameters</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0409">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A credit risk control unit must actively participate in the development, selection, implementation
and validation of rating models.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">actively participate in the development, selection, implementation and validation of rating models</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:A credit risk control unit">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">A credit risk control unit</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0410">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">It must assume oversight and supervision responsibilities for any models
used in the rating process, and ultimate responsibility for the ongoing review and alterations to rating
models.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">assume oversight and supervision responsibilities for any models used in the rating process, and ultimate responsibility for the ongoing review and alterations to rating models</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0411">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Internal audit or an equally independent function must review at least annually the bank’s rating
system and its operations, including the operations of the credit function and the estimation of PDs, LGDs
and EADs.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">review the bank’s rating system and its operations, including the operations of the credit function and the estimation of PDs, LGDs and EADs</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Internal audit or an equally independent function">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Internal audit or an equally independent function</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0411">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">annually</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0412">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Internal audit must
document its findings.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">document its findings</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Internal audit">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Internal audit</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0413">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Internal ratings and default and loss estimates must play an essential role in the credit approval,
risk management, internal capital allocations, and corporate governance functions of banks using the IRB
approach.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure internal ratings and default and loss estimates play an essential role in credit approval, risk management, internal capital allocations, and corporate governance functions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0414">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Where there
are such differences, a bank must document them and demonstrate their reasonableness to the supervisor.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">document differences and demonstrate their reasonableness to the supervisor</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0414">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where there are such differences</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0415">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A bank must have a credible track record in the use of internal ratings information.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have a credible track record in the use of internal ratings information</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0416">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Thus, the bank
must demonstrate that it has been using a rating system that was broadly in line with the minimum
requirements articulated in this document for at least the three years prior to qualification.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">demonstrate that it has been using a rating system that was broadly in line with the minimum requirements articulated in this document</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0416">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">prior to qualification</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0416">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">at least the three years</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0417">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A bank using
the advanced IRB approach must demonstrate that it has been estimating and employing LGDs and EADs
in a manner that is broadly consistent with the minimum requirements for use of own estimates of LGDs
and EADs for at least the three years prior to qualification.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">demonstrate that it has been estimating and employing LGDs and EADs in a manner that is broadly consistent with the minimum requirements for use of own estimates of LGDs and EADs</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:A bank using the advanced IRB approach">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">A bank using the advanced IRB approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0417">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">prior to qualification</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0417">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">at least the three years</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0418">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Generally, all
banks using the IRB approaches must estimate a PD25 for each internal borrower grade for corporate and
bank exposures or for each pool in the case of retail exposures.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">estimate a PD25 for each internal borrower grade for corporate and bank exposures or for each pool in the case of retail exposures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:banks using the IRB approaches">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">banks using the IRB approaches</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0418">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when using the IRB approaches</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0419">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">PD estimates must be a long-run average of one-year default rates for borrowers in the grade,
with the exception of retail exposures as set out in paragraph 233 and 234.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">be a long-run average of one-year default rates for borrowers in the grade</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:PD estimates">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">PD estimates</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0419">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">retail exposures as set out in paragraph 233 and 234</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0420">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks on the advanced approach must estimate an
appropriate LGD (as defined in paragraphs 235 to 240) for each of its facilities (or retail pools).</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">estimate an appropriate LGD for each of its facilities (or retail pools)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Banks on the advanced approach">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Banks on the advanced approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0420">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">as defined in paragraphs 235 to 240</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0421">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For
exposures subject to the advanced approach, banks must also estimate an appropriate long-run default-
weighted average EAD for each of its facilities as defined in paragraphs 241 and 242.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">estimate an appropriate long-run default-weighted average EAD for each of its facilities</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0421">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for exposures subject to the advanced approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0422">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For corporate and bank exposures, banks that do not
meet the requirements for own-estimates of EAD or LGD, above, must use the supervisory estimates of
these parameters.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use the supervisory estimates of these parameters</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:banks that do not meet the requirements for own-estimates of EAD or LGD">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">banks that do not meet the requirements for own-estimates of EAD or LGD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0422">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for corporate and bank exposures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0423">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Internal estimates of PD, LGD, and EAD must incorporate all relevant, material and available data,
information and methods.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">incorporate all relevant, material and available data, information and methods</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Internal estimates of PD, LGD, and EAD">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Internal estimates of PD, LGD, and EAD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0424">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Where internal or external data is used, the bank must demonstrate that its estimates are
representative of long run experience.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">demonstrate that its estimates are representative of long run experience</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0424">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where internal or external data is used</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0425">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Estimates must be grounded in historical experience and empirical evidence, and not based
purely on subjective or judgmental considerations.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be grounded in historical experience and empirical evidence, and not based purely on subjective or judgmental considerations</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Estimates">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Estimates</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0426">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Any changes in lending practice or the process for
pursuing recoveries over the observation period must be taken into account.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">take into account any changes in lending practice or the process for pursuing recoveries</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0426">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">over the observation period</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0427">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A bank’s estimates must
promptly reflect the implications of technical advances and new data and other information, as it becomes
available.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must promptly reflect the implications of technical advances and new data and other information in its estimates</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0427">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">as it becomes available</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0427">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">promptly</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0428">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must review their estimates on a yearly basis or more frequently.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">review their estimates</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0428">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">on a yearly basis or more frequently</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0429">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The bank must also demonstrate
that economic or market conditions that underlie the data are relevant to current and foreseeable
conditions.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">demonstrate that economic or market conditions that underlie the data are relevant to current and foreseeable conditions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0429">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">current and foreseeable conditions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0430">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For estimates of LGD and EAD, banks must take into account paragraphs 235 to 251.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">take into account paragraphs 235 to 251</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0430">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for estimates of LGD and EAD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0431">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The
number of exposures in the sample and the data period used for quantification must be sufficient to
provide the bank with confidence in the accuracy and robustness of its estimates.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure the number of exposures in the sample and the data period used for quantification are sufficient to provide confidence in the accuracy and robustness of its estimates</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0431">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for quantification of estimates</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0432">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The estimation technique
must perform well in out-of-sample tests.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">perform well in out-of-sample tests</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0432">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">during estimation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0433">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In order
to avoid over-optimism, a bank must add to its estimates a margin of conservatism that is related to the
likely range of errors.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">add to its estimates a margin of conservatism that is related to the likely range of errors</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0433">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in order to avoid over-optimism</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0434">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Where methods and data are less satisfactory and the likely range of errors is larger,
the margin of conservatism must be larger.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">the margin of conservatism must be larger</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0434">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where methods and data are less satisfactory and the likely range of errors is larger</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0435">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">However, in such cases banks must demonstrate to their supervisors that appropriate adjustments have
been made to achieve broad equivalence to the data without such flexibility.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">demonstrate to their supervisors that appropriate adjustments have been made to achieve broad equivalence to the data without such flexibility</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0435">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in such cases</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0436">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Data collected beyond the
date of implementation must conform to the minimum standards unless otherwise stated.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must conform to the minimum standards</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Data collected">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Data collected</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0436">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">beyond the date of implementation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0436">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">unless otherwise stated</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0437">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The obligor is past due more than 90 days on any material credit obligation to the banking
group.26 Overdrafts will be considered as being past due once the customer has breached an
advised limit or been advised of a limit smaller than current outstandings.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">be considered past due on any material credit obligation to the banking group</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:obligor">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">obligor</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0437">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">overdrafts when the customer has breached an advised limit or been advised of a limit smaller than current outstandings</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0437">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">more than 90 days</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0438">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The elements to be taken as indications of unlikeliness to pay include:
• The bank puts the credit obligation on non-accrued status.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">put the credit obligation on non-accrued status</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0438">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">as an indication of unlikeliness to pay</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0439">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The bank sells the credit obligation at a material credit-related economic loss.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">sells the credit obligation at a material credit-related economic loss</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0439">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">material</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0440">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The bank consents to a distressed restructuring of the credit obligation where this is likely to
result in a diminished financial obligation caused by the material forgiveness, or postponement,
of principal, interest or (where relevant) fees.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">consents to a distressed restructuring of the credit obligation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0440">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where this is likely to result in a diminished financial obligation caused by the material forgiveness, or postponement, of principal, interest or (where relevant) fees</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0441">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The bank has filed for the obligor’s bankruptcy or a similar order in respect of the obligor’s credit
obligation to the banking group.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">has filed for the obligor’s bankruptcy or a similar order in respect of the obligor’s credit obligation to the banking group</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0442">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The obligor has sought or has been placed in bankruptcy or similar protection where this would
avoid or delay repayment of the credit obligation to the banking group.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">has sought or has been placed in bankruptcy or similar protection</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0442">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where this would avoid or delay repayment of the credit obligation to the banking group</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0443">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">National supervisors will provide appropriate guidance as to how these elements must be
implemented and monitored.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">provide appropriate guidance as to how these elements must be implemented and monitored</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0444">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">As such, default by a borrower on one obligation does not require
a bank to treat all other obligations to the banking group as defaulted.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">treat all other obligations to the banking group as defaulted</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0444">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">default by a borrower on one obligation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0444">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">a bank is not required to treat all other obligations as defaulted</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0445">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A bank must record actual defaults on IRB exposure classes using this reference definition.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">record actual defaults on IRB exposure classes</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0445">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">using this reference definition</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0446">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A bank
must also use the reference definition for its estimation of PDs, and (where relevant) LGDs and EADs.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must also use the reference definition for its estimation of PDs, and (where relevant) LGDs and EADs</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0446">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where relevant</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0447">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">However, in such cases, banks must
demonstrate to their supervisors that appropriate adjustments to the data have been made to achieve
broad equivalence with the reference definition.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">demonstrate to their supervisors that appropriate adjustments to the data have been made to achieve broad equivalence with the reference definition</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0447">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in such cases</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0448">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Basel III: Finalising post-crisis reforms 93
estimates beyond the date of implementation of this Framework must be consistent with the reference
definition.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">Estimates beyond the date of implementation of this Framework must be consistent with the reference definition</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0448">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">Beyond the date of implementation of this Framework</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0449">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">If the bank considers that a previously defaulted exposure’s status is such that no trigger of the
reference definition any longer applies, the bank must rate the borrower and estimate LGD as they would
for a non-defaulted facility.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">rate the borrower and estimate LGD as they would for a non-defaulted facility</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0449">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">the bank considers that a previously defaulted exposure’s status is such that no trigger of the reference definition any longer applies</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0450">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The bank must have clearly articulated and documented policies in respect of the counting of
days past due, in particular in respect of the re-ageing of the facilities and the granting of extensions,
deferrals, renewals and rewrites to existing accounts.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must have clearly articulated and documented policies in respect of the counting of days past due, in particular in respect of the re-ageing of the facilities and the granting of extensions, deferrals, renewals and rewrites to existing accounts</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0450">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in respect of the counting of days past due, in particular in respect of the re-ageing of the facilities and the granting of extensions, deferrals, renewals and rewrites to existing accounts</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0451">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">At a minimum, the re-ageing policy must include: (a)
approval authorities and reporting requirements;</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">include approval authorities and reporting requirements</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the re-ageing policy">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the re-ageing policy</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0451">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">at a minimum</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0452">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">These policies must be
applied consistently over time, and must support the ‘use test’ (ie if a bank treats a re-aged exposure in a
similar fashion to other delinquent exposures more than the past-due cut off point, this exposure must be
recorded as in default for IRB purposes).</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">record exposure as in default for IRB purposes if treated in a similar fashion to other delinquent exposures beyond the past-due cut off point</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0452">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if a bank treats a re-aged exposure in a similar fashion to other delinquent exposures more than the past-due cut off point</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0453">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Authorised overdrafts must be subject to a credit limit set by the bank and brought to the
knowledge of the client.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">set a credit limit on authorised overdrafts and bring it to the knowledge of the client</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0453">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when providing authorised overdrafts</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0454">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Any break of this limit must be monitored;</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">monitor any break of the limit</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0454">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">break of the limit</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0455">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must have in place rigorous
internal policies for assessing the creditworthiness of customers who are offered overdraft accounts.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have in place rigorous internal policies for assessing the creditworthiness of customers who are offered overdraft accounts</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0455">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">customers who are offered overdraft accounts</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0456">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">This must include material discount effects and material
direct and indirect costs associated with collecting on the exposure.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">include material discount effects and material direct and indirect costs associated with collecting on the exposure</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0456">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if the effects and costs are material</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0457">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must not simply measure the
loss recorded in accounting records, although they must be able to compare accounting and economic
losses.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must not simply measure the loss recorded in accounting records</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0457">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">although they must be able to compare accounting and economic losses</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0458">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The bank’s own workout and collection expertise significantly influences their recovery rates and
must be reflected in their LGD estimates, but adjustments to estimates for such expertise must be
conservative until the bank has sufficient internal empirical evidence of the impact of its expertise.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">reflect own workout and collection expertise in LGD estimates</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0458">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when the bank's expertise significantly influences recovery rates</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0458">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">adjustments to estimates for such expertise need not be conservative once the bank has sufficient internal empirical evidence of the impact of its expertise</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0459">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must use information and techniques that take appropriate account of the long-run
experience when estimating the average PD for each rating grade.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use information and techniques that take appropriate account of the long-run experience when estimating the average PD for each rating grade</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0459">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when estimating the average PD for each rating grade</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0460">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must recognise the importance of judgmental considerations in combining results of
techniques and in making adjustments for limitations of techniques and information.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">recognise the importance of judgmental considerations in combining results of techniques and in making adjustments for limitations of techniques and information</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0461">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A bank must
demonstrate in its analysis that the estimates are reflective of underwriting standards and of any
differences in the rating system that generated the data and the current rating system.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">demonstrate in its analysis that the estimates are reflective of underwriting standards and of any differences in the rating system that generated the data and the current rating system</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0462">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Where
only limited data are available, or where underwriting standards or rating systems have changed,
the bank must add a greater margin of conservatism in its estimate of PD.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">add a greater margin of conservatism in its estimate of PD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0462">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">only limited data are available, or where underwriting standards or rating systems have changed</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0463">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A bank must demonstrate that the internal rating
systems and criteria of other banks in the pool are comparable with its own.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">demonstrate that the internal rating systems and criteria of other banks in the pool are comparable with its own</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0463">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when participating in a pool of banks</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0464">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Mappings must be based on a comparison of
internal rating criteria to the criteria used by the external institution and on a comparison of the
internal and external ratings of any common borrowers.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be based on a comparison of internal rating criteria to the criteria used by the external institution and on a comparison of the internal and external ratings of any common borrowers</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Mappings">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Mappings</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0465">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Biases or inconsistencies in the mapping
approach or underlying data must be avoided.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">avoid biases or inconsistencies in the mapping approach or underlying data</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0466">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The external institution’s criteria underlying the
data used for quantification must be oriented to the risk of the borrower and not reflect
transaction characteristics.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">orient the criteria underlying the data used for quantification to the risk of the borrower</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:external institution">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">external institution</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0466">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">data used for quantification</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0467">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The bank’s analysis must include a comparison of the default
definitions used, subject to the requirements in paragraph 220 to 225.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">include a comparison of the default definitions used</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0467">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">subject to the requirements in paragraph 220 to 225</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0468">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The bank must document
the basis for the mapping.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">document the basis for the mapping</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0469">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The bank’s use of default probability models for this purpose must meet the standards
specified in paragraph 185.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use of default probability models must meet the standards specified in paragraph 185</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0469">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for this purpose</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0470">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For all methods above, banks must estimate a PD for each rating grade based on the observed historical
average one-year default rate that is a simple average based on number of obligors (count weighted).</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">estimate a PD for each rating grade based on the observed historical average one-year default rate that is a simple average based on number of obligors (count weighted)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0470">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for all methods above</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0471">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Irrespective of whether a bank is using external, internal, or pooled data sources, or a combination
of the three, for its PD estimation, the length of the underlying historical observation period used must be
at least five years for at least one source.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use a historical observation period of at least five years for at least one data source for PD estimation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0471">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when using external, internal, or pooled data sources, or a combination of the three, for PD estimation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0471">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">five years</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0472">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">If the available observation period spans a longer period for any
source, and this data are relevant and material, this longer period must be used.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use the longer observation period</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0472">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if the available observation period spans a longer period for any source and this data are relevant and material</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0473">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Given the bank-specific basis of assigning exposures to pools, banks must regard internal data
as the primary source of information for estimating loss characteristics.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">regard internal data as the primary source of information for estimating loss characteristics</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0473">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">given the bank-specific basis of assigning exposures to pools</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0474">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In all cases banks must
use all relevant and material data sources as points of comparison.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use all relevant and material data sources as points of comparison</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0474">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in all cases</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0475">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In either case, it is important to recognise that the LGD used for the IRB capital
calculation cannot be less than the long-run default-weighted average loss rate given default and must
be consistent with the concepts defined in paragraph 235.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure the LGD used for the IRB capital calculation is not less than the long-run default-weighted average loss rate given default and is consistent with the concepts defined in paragraph 235</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:banks using IRB approach">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">banks using IRB approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0475">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when calculating IRB capital</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0475">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">LGD cannot be less than the long-run default-weighted average loss rate given default</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0476">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Irrespective of whether banks are using external, internal, pooled data sources, or a combination
of the three, for their estimation of loss characteristics, the length of the underlying historical observation
period used must be at least five years.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use a historical observation period of at least five years for estimation of loss characteristics</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0476">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when using external, internal, pooled data sources, or a combination of the three</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0476">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">five years</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0477">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">If the available observation spans a longer period for any source,
and these data are relevant, this longer period must be used.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use the longer period</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the entity making the observation">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the entity making the observation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0477">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if the available observation spans a longer period for any source and these data are relevant</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0478">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A bank must estimate an LGD for each facility that aims to reflect economic downturn conditions
where necessary to capture the relevant risks.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">estimate an LGD for each facility</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0478">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where necessary to capture the relevant risks</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0479">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In addition, a bank must take into account the potential for
the LGD of the facility to be higher than the default-weighted average during a period when credit losses
are substantially higher than average.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">take into account the potential for the LGD of the facility to be higher than the default-weighted average</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0479">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">during a period when credit losses are substantially higher than average</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0480">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In its analysis, the bank must consider the extent of any dependence between the risk of the
borrower and that of the collateral or collateral provider.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">consider the extent of any dependence between the risk of the borrower and that of the collateral or collateral provider</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0480">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in its analysis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0481">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Cases where there is a significant degree of
dependence must be addressed in a conservative manner.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">address cases in a conservative manner</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0481">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where there is a significant degree of dependence</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0482">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Any currency mismatch between the underlying
obligation and the collateral must also be considered and treated conservatively in the bank’s assessment
of LGD.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">consider and treat conservatively the currency mismatch between the underlying obligation and the collateral in the assessment of LGD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0482">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if there is a currency mismatch between the underlying obligation and the collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0483">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">LGD estimates must be grounded in historical recovery rates and, when applicable, must not
solely be based on the collateral’s estimated market value.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be grounded in historical recovery rates</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:LGD estimates">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">LGD estimates</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0483">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when applicable</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0483">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">must not solely be based on the collateral’s estimated market value</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0484">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">To the extent that
LGD estimates take into account the existence of collateral, banks must establish internal requirements for
collateral management, operational procedures, legal certainty and risk management process that are
generally consistent with those required for the foundation IRB approach.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">establish internal requirements for collateral management, operational procedures, legal certainty and risk management process</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0484">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to the extent that LGD estimates take into account the existence of collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0485">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For each defaulted asset, the bank must also
construct its best estimate of the expected loss on that asset based on current economic circumstances
and facility status.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">construct its best estimate of the expected loss on that asset</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0485">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for each defaulted asset, based on current economic circumstances and facility status</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0486">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Instances where
the best estimate of expected loss on a defaulted asset is less than the sum of specific provisions and
partial charge-offs on that asset will attract supervisory scrutiny and must be justified by the bank.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">justify instances where the best estimate of expected loss on a defaulted asset is less than the sum of specific provisions and partial charge-offs on that asset</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0486">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when the best estimate of expected loss on a defaulted asset is less than the sum of specific provisions and partial charge-offs on that asset</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0487">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Estimates of LGD must be based on a minimum data observation period that should ideally cover
at least one complete economic cycle but must in any case be no shorter than a period of seven years for
at least one source.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">be based on a minimum data observation period</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Estimates of LGD">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Estimates of LGD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0487">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">should ideally cover at least one complete economic cycle</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0487">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">no shorter than a period of seven years for at least one source</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0488">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">If the available observation period spans a longer period for any source, and the data
are relevant, this longer period must be used.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use the longer observation period</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:regulated entity responsible for data observation">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">regulated entity responsible for data observation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0488">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if the available observation period spans a longer period for any source and the data are relevant</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0489">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The
less data a bank has, the more conservative it must be in its estimation.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">be more conservative in its estimation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0489">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">the less data a bank has</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0490">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For on-balance sheet items, banks must estimate EAD at no less
than the current drawn amount, subject to recognising the effects of on-balance sheet netting as specified
in the foundation approach.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">estimate EAD at no less than the current drawn amount</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0490">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for on-balance sheet items, subject to recognising the effects of on-balance sheet netting as specified in the foundation approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0490">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">no less than the current drawn amount</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0491">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks using the advanced approach must have established procedures in place for the
estimation of EAD for off-balance sheet items.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have established procedures in place for the estimation of EAD for off-balance sheet items</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Banks using the advanced approach">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Banks using the advanced approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0492">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">These must specify the estimates of EAD to be used for
each facility type.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">specify the estimates of EAD to be used for each facility type</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:These">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">These</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0493">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Where estimates of EAD differ by facility
type, the delineation of these facilities must be clear and unambiguous.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be clear and unambiguous</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the delineation of these facilities">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the delineation of these facilities</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0493">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">Where estimates of EAD differ by facility type</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0494">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Under the advanced approach, banks must assign an estimate of EAD for each eligible facility.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">assign an estimate of EAD for each eligible facility</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0494">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">under the advanced approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0495">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">It
must be an estimate of the long-run default-weighted average EAD for similar facilities and borrowers
over a sufficiently long period of time, but with a margin of conservatism appropriate to the likely range
of errors in the estimate.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">estimate the long-run default-weighted average EAD for similar facilities and borrowers over a sufficiently long period of time with a margin of conservatism appropriate to the likely range of errors in the estimate</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0495">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for similar facilities and borrowers</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0496">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">If a positive correlation can reasonably be expected between the default
frequency and the magnitude of EAD, the EAD estimate must incorporate a larger margin of conservatism.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">incorporate a larger margin of conservatism</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the EAD estimate">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the EAD estimate</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0496">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if a positive correlation can reasonably be expected between the default frequency and the magnitude of EAD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0497">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Moreover, for exposures for which EAD estimates are volatile over the economic cycle, the bank must use
EAD estimates that are appropriate for an economic downturn, if these are more conservative than the
long-run average.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use EAD estimates that are appropriate for an economic downturn</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0497">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for exposures for which EAD estimates are volatile over the economic cycle and if downturn EAD estimates are more conservative than the long-run average</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0498">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The criteria by which estimates of EAD are derived must be plausible and intuitive, and represent
what the bank believes to be the material drivers of EAD.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">derive estimates of EAD using criteria that are plausible and intuitive and represent the material drivers of EAD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0498">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when deriving estimates of EAD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0499">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The choices must be supported by credible
internal analysis by the bank.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">support the choices by credible internal analysis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0500">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The bank must be able to provide a breakdown of its EAD experience by the
factors it sees as the drivers of EAD.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">provide a breakdown of its EAD experience by the factors it sees as the drivers of EAD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0501">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A bank must use all relevant and material information in its derivation
of EAD estimates.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must use all relevant and material information in its derivation of EAD estimates</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0502">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Across facility types, a bank must review its estimates of EAD when material new
information comes to light and at least on an annual basis.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">review its estimates of EAD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0502">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when material new information comes to light and at least on an annual basis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0503">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Due consideration must be paid by the bank to its specific policies and strategies adopted in
respect of account monitoring and payment processing.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">pay due consideration to its specific policies and strategies</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0503">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in respect of account monitoring and payment processing</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0504">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The bank must also consider its ability and
willingness to prevent further drawings in circumstances short of payment default, such as covenant
violations or other technical default events.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">consider its ability and willingness to prevent further drawings</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0504">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">circumstances short of payment default, such as covenant violations or other technical default events</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0505">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must also have adequate systems and procedures in
place to monitor facility amounts, current outstandings against committed lines and changes in
outstandings per borrower and per grade.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have adequate systems and procedures in place to monitor facility amounts, current outstandings against committed lines and changes in outstandings per borrower and per grade</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0506">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The bank must be able to monitor outstanding balances on a
daily basis.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">monitor outstanding balances</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0506">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">on a daily basis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0507">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks’ EAD estimates must be developed using a 12-month fixed-horizon approach;</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">develop EAD estimates using a 12-month fixed-horizon approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0507">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">12-month</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0508">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">ie for each
observation in the reference data set, default outcomes must be linked to relevant obligor and facility
characteristics twelve months prior to default.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be linked to relevant obligor and facility characteristics twelve months prior to default</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:default outcomes">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">default outcomes</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0508">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for each observation in the reference data set</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0509">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks
should ensure that their EAD estimates are effectively quarantined from the potential effects of this region
of instability.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure that their EAD estimates are effectively quarantined from the potential effects of this region of instability</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0509">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">this region of instability</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0510">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">EAD reference data must not be capped to the principal amount outstanding or facility limits.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must not be capped to the principal amount outstanding or facility limits</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:EAD reference data">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">EAD reference data</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0511">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For transactions that expose banks to counterparty credit risk, estimates of EAD must fulfil the
requirements set forth in the counterparty credit risk standards.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">estimate EAD in accordance with counterparty credit risk standards</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0511">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for transactions that expose banks to counterparty credit risk</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0512">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Estimates of EAD must be based on a time period that must ideally cover a complete economic
cycle but must in any case be no shorter than a period of seven years.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be based on a time period that covers a complete economic cycle</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Estimates of EAD">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Estimates of EAD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0512">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">ideally cover a complete economic cycle</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0512">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">no shorter than a period of seven years</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0513">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">If the available observation period
spans a longer period for any source, and the data are relevant, this longer period must be used.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use the longer observation period</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0513">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if the available observation period spans a longer period for any source and the data are relevant</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0514">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">EAD
estimates must be calculated using a default-weighted average and not a time-weighted average.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">estimates must be calculated using a default-weighted average</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:EAD">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">EAD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0514">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">not a time-weighted average</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0515">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The
less data a bank has, the more conservative it must be in its estimation.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">be more conservative in its estimation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0515">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">the less data a bank has</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0516">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For retail exposures, where guarantees
exist, either in support of an individual obligation or a pool of exposures, a bank may reflect the risk-
reducing effect either through its estimates of PD or LGD, provided this is done consistently.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">reflect the risk-reducing effect either through its estimates of PD or LGD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0516">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for retail exposures where guarantees exist, either in support of an individual obligation or a pool of exposures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0516">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">provided this is done consistently</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0517">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In adopting
one or the other technique, a bank must adopt a consistent approach, both across types of guarantees
and over time.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">adopt a consistent approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0517">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in adopting one or the other technique</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0518">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In all cases, both the borrower and all recognised guarantors must be assigned a borrower rating
at the outset and on an ongoing basis.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be assigned a borrower rating</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the borrower and all recognised guarantors">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the borrower and all recognised guarantors</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0518">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">at the outset and on an ongoing basis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0519">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A bank must follow all minimum requirements for assigning
borrower ratings set out in this document, including the regular monitoring of the guarantor’s condition
and ability and willingness to honour its obligations.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">follow all minimum requirements for assigning borrower ratings</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0519">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">as set out in this document, including the regular monitoring of the guarantor’s condition and ability and willingness to honour its obligations</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0520">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Consistent with the requirements in paragraphs 198
and 199, a bank must retain all relevant information on the borrower absent the guarantee and the
guarantor.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">retain all relevant information on the borrower absent the guarantee and the guarantor</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0520">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">Consistent with the requirements in paragraphs 198 and 199</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0521">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">As such, the adjusted risk weight must not reflect the risk mitigation of “double
default.”
Basel III: Finalising post-crisis reforms 99
255.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must not reflect the risk mitigation of 'double default'</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0522">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The bank must, however, have clearly
specified criteria for the types of guarantors it will recognise for regulatory capital purposes.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have clearly specified criteria for the types of guarantors it will recognise for regulatory capital purposes</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0523">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The guarantee must be evidenced in writing, non-cancellable on the part of the guarantor, in
force until the debt is satisfied in full (to the extent of the amount and tenor of the guarantee) and legally
enforceable against the guarantor in a jurisdiction where the guarantor has assets to attach and enforce a
judgement.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">evidence the guarantee in writing, ensure it is non-cancellable, in force until the debt is satisfied in full, and legally enforceable</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0523">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">the guarantee must cover the extent of the amount and tenor of the guarantee</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0523">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">until the debt is satisfied in full</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0524">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The guarantee must also be unconditional;</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">be unconditional</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The guarantee">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The guarantee</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0525">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A bank must have clearly specified criteria for adjusting borrower grades or LGD estimates (or in
the case of retail and eligible purchased receivables, the process of allocating exposures to pools) to reflect
the impact of guarantees for regulatory capital purposes.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must have clearly specified criteria for adjusting borrower grades or LGD estimates (or in the case of retail and eligible purchased receivables, the process of allocating exposures to pools) to reflect the impact of guarantees for regulatory capital purposes</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0525">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for regulatory capital purposes</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0525">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">in the case of retail and eligible purchased receivables, the process of allocating exposures to pools</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0526">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">These criteria must be as detailed as the criteria
for assigning exposures to grades consistent with paragraphs 177 and 178, and must follow all minimum
requirements for assigning borrower or facility ratings set out in this document.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure criteria for assigning exposures to grades are as detailed as those consistent with paragraphs 177 and 178 and follow all minimum requirements for assigning borrower or facility ratings</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0526">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">criteria for assigning exposures to grades</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0527">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The criteria must be plausible and intuitive, and must address the guarantor’s ability and
willingness to perform under the guarantee.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be plausible and intuitive, and must address the guarantor’s ability and willingness to perform under the guarantee</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0528">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The criteria must also address the likely timing of any
payments and the degree to which the guarantor’s ability to perform under the guarantee is correlated
with the borrower’s ability to repay.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">address the likely timing of any payments and the degree to which the guarantor’s ability to perform under the guarantee is correlated with the borrower’s ability to repay</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0528">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when establishing the criteria</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0529">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The bank’s criteria must also consider the extent to which residual risk
to the borrower remains, for example a currency mismatch between the guarantee and the underlying
exposure.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must consider the extent to which residual risk to the borrower remains</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0529">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for example a currency mismatch between the guarantee and the underlying exposure</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0530">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In adjusting borrower grades or LGD estimates (or in the case of retail and eligible purchased
receivables, the process of allocating exposures to pools), banks must take all relevant available
information into account.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">take all relevant available information into account</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0530">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in adjusting borrower grades or LGD estimates, or in the case of retail and eligible purchased receivables, the process of allocating exposures to pools</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0531">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The criteria used for assigning adjusted
borrower grades or LGD estimates (or pools) for exposures hedged with credit derivatives must require
that the asset on which the protection is based (the reference asset) cannot be different from the
underlying asset, unless the conditions outlined in the foundation approach are met.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">require that the asset on which the protection is based (the reference asset) cannot be different from the underlying asset</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The criteria used for assigning adjusted borrower grades or LGD estimates (or pools) for exposures hedged with credit derivatives">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The criteria used for assigning adjusted borrower grades or LGD estimates (or pools) for exposures hedged with credit derivatives</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0531">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">unless the conditions outlined in the foundation approach are met</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0531">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">if the conditions outlined in the foundation approach are met</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0532">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In addition, the criteria must address the payout structure of the credit derivative and
conservatively assess the impact this has on the level and timing of recoveries.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">address the payout structure of the credit derivative and conservatively assess the impact this has on the level and timing of recoveries</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the criteria">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the criteria</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0533">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The bank must also consider
the extent to which other forms of residual risk remain.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">consider the extent to which other forms of residual risk remain</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0534">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The following minimum requirements for risk quantification must be satisfied for any purchased
receivables (corporate or retail) making use of the top-down treatment of default risk and/or the IRB
treatments of dilution risk.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">Satisfy minimum requirements for risk quantification</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Institutions purchasing receivables">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Institutions purchasing receivables</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0534">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">When using top-down treatment of default risk and/or IRB treatments of dilution risk for purchased receivables</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0535">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In addition, methods and data for
estimating PD, LGD, and EL must comply with the existing risk quantification standards for retail exposures.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">comply with the existing risk quantification standards for retail exposures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:methods and data for estimating PD, LGD, and EL">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">methods and data for estimating PD, LGD, and EL</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0535">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for retail exposures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0536">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The purchasing bank must determine whether the data provided
by the seller are consistent with expectations agreed upon by both parties concerning, for example, the
type, volume and on-going quality of receivables purchased.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">determine whether the data provided by the seller are consistent with expectations agreed upon by both parties</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0536">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">concerning, for example, the type, volume and on-going quality of receivables purchased</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0537">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The structure of the facility must ensure that under all foreseeable circumstances the bank has
effective ownership and control of the cash remittances from the receivables, including incidences of seller
or servicer distress and bankruptcy.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure that the bank has effective ownership and control of the cash remittances from the receivables</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The structure of the facility">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The structure of the facility</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0537">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">under all foreseeable circumstances, including incidences of seller or servicer distress and bankruptcy</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0538">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">When the obligor makes payments directly to a seller or servicer, the
bank must verify regularly that payments are forwarded completely and within the contractually agreed
terms.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">verify regularly that payments are forwarded completely and within the contractually agreed terms</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0538">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when the obligor makes payments directly to a seller or servicer</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0539">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The bank must be able to monitor both the quality of the receivables and the financial condition
of the seller and servicer.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">be able to monitor both the quality of the receivables and the financial condition of the seller and servicer</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0540">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In particular:
• The bank must (a) assess the correlation among the quality of the receivables and the financial
condition of both the seller and servicer, and (b) have in place internal policies and procedures
that provide adequate safeguards to protect against such contingencies, including the
assignment of an internal risk rating for each seller and servicer.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">assess the correlation among the quality of the receivables and the financial condition of both the seller and servicer; have in place internal policies and procedures that provide adequate safeguards to protect against such contingencies, including the assignment of an internal risk rating for each seller and servicer</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0541">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The bank must have clear and effective policies and procedures for determining seller and
servicer eligibility.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have clear and effective policies and procedures for determining seller and servicer eligibility</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0542">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The bank or its agent must conduct periodic reviews of sellers and servicers in
Basel III: Finalising post-crisis reforms 101
order to verify the accuracy of reports from the seller/servicer, detect fraud or operational
weaknesses, and verify the quality of the seller’s credit policies and servicer’s collection policies
and procedures.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">conduct periodic reviews of sellers and servicers</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:bank or its agent">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">bank or its agent</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0542">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in order to verify the accuracy of reports from the seller/servicer, detect fraud or operational weaknesses, and verify the quality of the seller’s credit policies and servicer’s collection policies and procedures</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0543">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The findings of these reviews must be well documented.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">document the findings of the reviews</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0543">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">these reviews</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0544">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The bank must have the ability to assess the characteristics of the receivables pool, including: (a)
over-advances;</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have the ability to assess the characteristics of the receivables pool</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0544">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">including over-advances</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0545">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The bank must have effective policies and procedures for monitoring on an aggregate basis
single-obligor concentrations both within and across receivables pools.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have effective policies and procedures for monitoring on an aggregate basis single-obligor concentrations both within and across receivables pools</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0546">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The bank must receive timely and sufficiently detailed reports of receivables ageings and dilutions
to (a) ensure compliance with the bank’s eligibility criteria and advancing policies governing
purchased receivables, and (b) provide an effective means with which to monitor and confirm the
seller’s terms of sale (eg invoice date ageing) and dilution.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">receive timely and sufficiently detailed reports of receivables ageings and dilutions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0546">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to (a) ensure compliance with the bank’s eligibility criteria and advancing policies governing purchased receivables, and (b) provide an effective means with which to monitor and confirm the seller’s terms of sale (eg invoice date ageing) and dilution</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0546">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">timely</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0547">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The bank must have clear and effective policies and procedures governing the control of
receivables, credit, and cash.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have clear and effective policies and procedures governing the control of receivables, credit, and cash</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0548">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In particular,
• Written internal policies must specify all material elements of the receivables purchase
programme, including the advancing rates, eligible collateral, necessary documentation,
concentration limits, and how cash receipts are to be handled.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">specify all material elements of the receivables purchase programme</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Written internal policies">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Written internal policies</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0548">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">including the advancing rates, eligible collateral, necessary documentation, concentration limits, and how cash receipts are to be handled</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0549">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• Internal systems must ensure that funds are advanced only against specified supporting collateral
and documentation (such as servicer attestations, invoices, shipping documents, etc).</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure that funds are advanced only against specified supporting collateral and documentation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Internal systems">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Internal systems</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0549">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when advancing funds</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0550">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must have a robust system in place to validate the accuracy and consistency of rating
systems, processes, and the estimation of all relevant risk components.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have a robust system in place to validate the accuracy and consistency of rating systems, processes, and the estimation of all relevant risk components</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0551">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A bank must demonstrate to its
supervisor that the internal validation process enables it to assess the performance of internal rating and
risk estimation systems consistently and meaningfully.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">demonstrate to its supervisor that the internal validation process enables it to assess the performance of internal rating and risk estimation systems consistently and meaningfully</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0552">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must regularly compare realised default rates with estimated PDs for each grade and be
able to demonstrate that the realised default rates are within the expected range for that grade.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">regularly compare realised default rates with estimated PDs for each grade and be able to demonstrate that the realised default rates are within the expected range for that grade</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0552">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">within the expected range for that grade</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0552">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">regularly</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0553">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks
using the advanced IRB approach must complete such analysis for their estimates of LGDs and EADs.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">complete such analysis for their estimates of LGDs and EADs</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0554">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Such
comparisons must make use of historical data that are over as long a period as possible.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">make use of historical data that are over as long a period as possible</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:comparisons">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">comparisons</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0555">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The methods and
data used in such comparisons by the bank must be clearly documented by the bank.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">clearly document the methods and data used in such comparisons</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0555">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in such comparisons</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0556">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">This analysis and
documentation must be updated at least annually.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">update the analysis and documentation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0556">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">at least annually</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0557">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must also use other quantitative validation tools and comparisons with relevant external
data sources.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use other quantitative validation tools and comparisons with relevant external data sources</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0558">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The analysis must be based on data that are appropriate to the portfolio, are updated
regularly, and cover a relevant observation period.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be based on data that are appropriate to the portfolio, are updated regularly, and cover a relevant observation period</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The analysis">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The analysis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0559">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks’ internal assessments of the performance of their
own rating systems must be based on long data histories, covering a range of economic conditions, and
ideally one or more complete business cycles.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">conduct internal assessments of the performance of their own rating systems</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0559">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">based on long data histories, covering a range of economic conditions, and ideally one or more complete business cycles</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0560">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must demonstrate that quantitative testing methods and other validation methods do not
vary systematically with the economic cycle.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">demonstrate that quantitative testing methods and other validation methods do not vary systematically with the economic cycle</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0561">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Changes in methods and data (both data sources and periods
covered) must be clearly and thoroughly documented.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">document changes in methods and data clearly and thoroughly</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The entity making changes in methods and data">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The entity making changes in methods and data</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0561">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when there are changes in methods and data (including data sources and periods covered)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0562">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must have well-articulated internal standards for situations where deviations in realised
PDs, LGDs and EADs from expectations become significant enough to call the validity of the estimates into
question.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have well-articulated internal standards for situations where deviations in realised PDs, LGDs and EADs from expectations become significant enough to call the validity of the estimates into question</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0562">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where deviations in realised PDs, LGDs and EADs from expectations become significant enough to call the validity of the estimates into question</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0563">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">These standards must take account of business cycles and similar systematic variability in default
experiences.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">take account of business cycles and similar systematic variability in default experiences</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:These standards">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">These standards</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0564">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Where realised values continue to be higher than expected values, banks must revise
estimates upward to reflect their default and loss experience.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">revise estimates upward to reflect their default and loss experience</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0564">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where realised values continue to be higher than expected values</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0565">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks under the foundation IRB approach, which do not meet the requirements for own-
estimates of LGD and EAD, above, must meet the minimum requirements described in the standardised
approach to receive recognition for eligible financial collateral (as set out in the credit risk mitigation
section (Section D) of the standardised approach).</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must meet the minimum requirements described in the standardised approach to receive recognition for eligible financial collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Banks under the foundation IRB approach">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Banks under the foundation IRB approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0565">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">which do not meet the requirements for own-estimates of LGD and EAD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0566">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">They must meet the following additional minimum
requirements in order to receive recognition for additional collateral types.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">meet the following additional minimum requirements</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:They">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">They</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0566">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in order to receive recognition for additional collateral types</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0567">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">As such, repayment of the facility is not materially dependent on
any cash flow generated by the underlying CRE/RRE serving as collateral;29 and
• Additionally, the value of the collateral pledged must not be materially dependent on the
performance of the borrower.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure the value of the collateral pledged is not materially dependent on the performance of the borrower</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the borrower">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the borrower</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0567">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when pledging collateral for the facility</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0568">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• Legal enforceability: any claim on collateral taken must be legally enforceable in all relevant
jurisdictions, and any claim on collateral must be properly filed on a timely basis.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be legally enforceable in all relevant jurisdictions and properly filed on a timely basis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:any claim on collateral">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">any claim on collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0568">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">on a timely basis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0569">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Collateral
interests must reflect a perfected lien (ie all legal requirements for establishing the claim have
been fulfilled).</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">reflect a perfected lien</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Collateral interests">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Collateral interests</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0569">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">all legal requirements for establishing the claim have been fulfilled</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0570">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Furthermore, the collateral agreement and the legal process underpinning it must
be such that they provide for the bank to realise the value of the collateral within a reasonable
timeframe.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">provide for the bank to realise the value of the collateral within a reasonable timeframe</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the collateral agreement and the legal process underpinning it">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the collateral agreement and the legal process underpinning it</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0570">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">within a reasonable timeframe</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0571">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• Objective market value of collateral: the collateral must be valued at or less than the current fair
value under which the property could be sold under private contract between a willing seller and
an arm’s-length buyer on the date of valuation.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be valued at or less than the current fair value</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the collateral">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0571">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">under which the property could be sold under private contract between a willing seller and an arm’s-length buyer on the date of valuation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0571">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">on the date of valuation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0572">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In particular, two tests must be
fulfilled, namely that (i) losses stemming from commercial real estate lending up to the lower of 50% of the market value or
60% of loan-to value (LTV) based on mortgage-lending-value (MLV) must not exceed 0.3% of the outstanding loans in any
given year;</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure losses from commercial real estate lending do not exceed 0.3% of outstanding loans in any given year</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:entities engaged in commercial real estate lending">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">entities engaged in commercial real estate lending</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0572">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for loans up to the lower of 50% of the market value or 60% of loan-to-value (LTV) based on mortgage-lending-value (MLV)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0572">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">0.3%</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0572">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">in any given year</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0573">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">and that (ii) overall losses stemming from commercial real estate lending must not exceed 0.5% of the outstanding
loans in any given year.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure overall losses from commercial real estate lending do not exceed 0.5% of outstanding loans</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:financial institution">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">financial institution</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0573">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in any given year</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0573">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">0.5%</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0573">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">annually</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0574">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Countries
applying such a treatment must publicly disclose that these are met.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">publicly disclose that these are met</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Countries">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Countries</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0574">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">applying such a treatment</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0575">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A qualified professional
must evaluate the property when information indicates that the value of the collateral may have
declined materially relative to general market prices or when a credit event, such as default,
occurs.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">evaluate the property</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:A qualified professional">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">A qualified professional</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0575">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when information indicates that the value of the collateral may have declined materially relative to general market prices or when a credit event, such as default, occurs</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0576">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Where junior liens are recognised the bank must first take the haircut value
of the collateral, then reduce it by the sum of all loans with liens that rank higher than the junior
lien, the remaining value is the collateral that supports the loan with the junior lien.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">take the haircut value of the collateral, then reduce it by the sum of all loans with liens that rank higher than the junior lien, and use the remaining value as collateral that supports the loan with the junior lien</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0576">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where junior liens are recognised</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0577">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Additional collateral management requirements are as follows:
• The types of CRE and RRE collateral accepted by the bank and lending policies (advance rates)
when this type of collateral is taken must be clearly documented.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">clearly document the types of CRE and RRE collateral accepted and lending policies (advance rates) when this type of collateral is taken</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0577">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when this type of collateral is taken</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0578">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The bank must take steps to ensure that the property taken as collateral is adequately insured
against damage or deterioration.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">take steps to ensure that the property taken as collateral is adequately insured against damage or deterioration</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0579">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The bank must monitor on an ongoing basis the extent of any permissible prior claims (eg tax)
on the property.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">monitor on an ongoing basis the extent of any permissible prior claims on the property</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0579">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">prior claims are permissible (e.g., tax)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0579">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">on an ongoing basis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0580">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The bank must appropriately monitor the risk of environmental liability arising in respect of the
collateral, such as the presence of toxic material on a property.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">monitor the risk of environmental liability arising in respect of the collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0580">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">such as the presence of toxic material on a property</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0581">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The legal mechanism by which collateral is given must be robust and ensure that the lender has
clear rights over the proceeds from the collateral.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">Ensure the legal mechanism for giving collateral is robust and ensures the lender has clear rights over the proceeds</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The entity providing collateral">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The entity providing collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0582">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must take all steps necessary to fulfil local requirements in respect of the enforceability of
security interest, eg by registering a security interest with a registrar.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">take all steps necessary to fulfil local requirements in respect of the enforceability of security interest</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0582">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in respect of the enforceability of security interest</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0583">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">All documentation used in collateralised transactions must be binding on all parties and legally
enforceable in all relevant jurisdictions.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure that all documentation used is binding and legally enforceable</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:All parties involved in collateralised transactions">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">All parties involved in collateralised transactions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0583">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in all relevant jurisdictions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0584">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must have conducted sufficient legal review to verify this
and have a well-founded legal basis to reach this conclusion, and undertake such further review as
necessary to ensure continuing enforceability.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">conduct sufficient legal review to verify this and have a well-founded legal basis to reach this conclusion, and undertake further review as necessary to ensure continuing enforceability</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0584">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to verify this and ensure continuing enforceability</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0585">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The collateral arrangements must be properly documented, with a clear and robust procedure
for the timely collection of collateral proceeds.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be properly documented, with a clear and robust procedure for the timely collection of collateral proceeds</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The collateral arrangements">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The collateral arrangements</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0586">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks’ procedures should ensure that any legal conditions
required for declaring the default of the customer and timely collection of collateral are observed.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure that any legal conditions required for declaring the default of the customer and timely collection of collateral are observed</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0586">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when declaring the default of the customer and collecting collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0586">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">timely</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0587">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The bank must have a sound process for determining the credit risk in the receivables.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have a sound process for determining the credit risk in the receivables</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0588">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Where the bank
relies on the borrower to ascertain the credit risk of the customers, the bank must review the borrower’s
credit policy to ascertain its soundness and credibility.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">review the borrower’s credit policy to ascertain its soundness and credibility</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0588">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where the bank relies on the borrower to ascertain the credit risk of the customers</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0589">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The margin between the amount of the exposure and the value of the receivables must reflect all
appropriate factors, including the cost of collection, concentration within the receivables pool pledged by
an individual borrower, and potential concentration risk within the bank’s total exposures.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure the margin between the amount of the exposure and the value of the receivables reflects all appropriate factors</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The entity calculating the margin">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The entity calculating the margin</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0589">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when determining the margin for receivables pledged by an individual borrower</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0590">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The bank must maintain a continuous monitoring process that is appropriate for the specific
exposures (either immediate or contingent) attributable to the collateral to be utilised as a risk mitigant.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">maintain a continuous monitoring process that is appropriate for the specific exposures (either immediate or contingent) attributable to the collateral to be utilised as a risk mitigant</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0590">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">exposures (either immediate or contingent) attributable to the collateral to be utilised as a risk mitigant</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0591">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must carry out
106 Basel III: Finalising post-crisis reforms
a reassessment of this condition both periodically and when information indicates material
changes in the market.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">carry out a reassessment of this condition</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0591">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when information indicates material changes in the market</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0591">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">periodically</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0592">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must also demonstrate that the amount
they receive when collateral is realised does not deviate significantly from these market prices.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">demonstrate that the amount they receive when collateral is realised does not deviate significantly from market prices</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0592">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when collateral is realised</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0592">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">not deviate significantly from market prices</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0593">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In order for a given bank to receive recognition for additional physical collateral, it must meet all
the standards in paragraphs 283 and 284, subject to the following modifications.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">meet all the standards in paragraphs 283 and 284</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:a given bank">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">a given bank</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0593">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in order to receive recognition for additional physical collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0593">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">subject to the following modifications</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0594">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">As such, the bank must have priority over all
other lenders to the realised proceeds of the collateral.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have priority over all other lenders to the realised proceeds of the collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0595">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The loan agreement must include detailed descriptions of the collateral and the right to examine
and revalue the collateral whenever this is deemed necessary by the lending bank.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">include detailed descriptions of the collateral and the right to examine and revalue the collateral whenever this is deemed necessary by the lending bank</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The loan agreement">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The loan agreement</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0595">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">whenever this is deemed necessary by the lending bank</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0596">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The types of physical collateral accepted by the bank and policies and practices in respect of the
appropriate amount of each type of collateral relative to the exposure amount must be clearly
documented in internal credit policies and procedures and available for examination and/or audit
review.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">clearly document the types of physical collateral accepted and policies and practices regarding the appropriate amount of each type of collateral relative to the exposure amount in internal credit policies and procedures and make them available for examination and/or audit review</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0597">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• Bank credit policies with regard to the transaction structure must address appropriate collateral
requirements relative to the exposure amount, the ability to liquidate the collateral readily, the
ability to establish objectively a price or market value, the frequency with which the value can
readily be obtained (including a professional appraisal or valuation), and the volatility of the value
of the collateral.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">Address appropriate collateral requirements in credit policies with regard to the transaction structure</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0597">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">Relative to the exposure amount, the ability to liquidate the collateral readily, the ability to establish objectively a price or market value, the frequency with which the value can readily be obtained (including a professional appraisal or valuation), and the volatility of the value of the collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0598">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The periodic revaluation process must pay particular attention to “fashion-
sensitive” collateral to ensure that valuations are appropriately adjusted downward of fashion, or
model-year, obsolescence as well as physical obsolescence or deterioration.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">pay particular attention to 'fashion-sensitive' collateral to ensure that valuations are appropriately adjusted downward</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The periodic revaluation process">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The periodic revaluation process</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0598">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">of fashion, or model-year, obsolescence as well as physical obsolescence or deterioration</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0599">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• In cases of inventories (eg raw materials, work-in-process, finished goods, dealers’ inventories of
autos) and equipment, the periodic revaluation process must include physical inspection of the
collateral.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">include physical inspection of the collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the periodic revaluation process">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the periodic revaluation process</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0599">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in cases of inventories (e.g., raw materials, work-in-process, finished goods, dealers’ inventories of autos) and equipment</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0600">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The minimum
requirements for the collateral type must be met (CRE/RRE or other collateral).</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">meet the minimum requirements for the collateral type</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0600">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if the collateral type is CRE/RRE or other collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0600">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">minimum requirements</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0601">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In addition, the bank must
also meet the following standards:
• Robust risk management on the part of the lessor with respect to the location of the asset, the
use to which it is put, its age, and planned obsolescence;</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">meet the following standards: robust risk management on the part of the lessor with respect to the location of the asset, the use to which it is put, its age, and planned obsolescence</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0601">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">with respect to the location of the asset, the use to which it is put, its age, and planned obsolescence</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0602">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">and
• The difference between the rate of depreciation of the physical asset and the rate of amortisation
of the lease payments must not be so large as to overstate the CRM attributed to the leased
assets.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure the difference between the rate of depreciation of the physical asset and the rate of amortisation of the lease payments is not so large as to overstate the CRM attributed to the leased assets</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The entity calculating CRM for leased assets">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The entity calculating CRM for leased assets</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0602">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when calculating CRM attributed to leased assets</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0603">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In order to be eligible for the IRB approach, banks must meet the disclosure requirements set out
in Pillar 3.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">meet the disclosure requirements set out in Pillar 3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0603">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in order to be eligible for the IRB approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0604">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The capital requirement for CVA risk must be calculated by all banks involved in covered
transactions.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">calculate the capital requirement for CVA risk</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:all banks involved in covered transactions">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">all banks involved in covered transactions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0604">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">involvement in covered transactions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0605">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must use the BA-CVA unless they receive approval from their
relevant supervisory authority to use the SA-CVA.2
6.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use the BA-CVA</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0605">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">unless they receive approval from their relevant supervisory authority to use the SA-CVA</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0605">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">if they receive approval from their relevant supervisory authority to use the SA-CVA</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0606">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">CVA capital for all carved out netting sets
must be calculated via the BA-CVA.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">calculate CVA capital for all carved out netting sets</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0606">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for all carved out netting sets</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0607">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">If chosen, this treatment must be applied to the bank’s entire portfolio instead of
the BA-CVA or the SA-CVA.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">apply this treatment to the entire portfolio</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0607">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if chosen</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0607">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">instead of the BA-CVA or the SA-CVA</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0608">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Basel III: Finalising post-crisis reforms 109
• All external CVA hedges (whether eligible or not) that are covered transactions must be included
in the CVA calculation for the counterparty to the hedge.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be included in the CVA calculation for the counterparty to the hedge</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:All external CVA hedges">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">All external CVA hedges</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0608">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">that are covered transactions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0608">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">whether eligible or not</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0609">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• All eligible external CVA hedges must be excluded from a bank’s market risk capital charge
calculations in the trading book.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">exclude all eligible external CVA hedges from market risk capital charge calculations in the trading book</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0609">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if the hedges are eligible external CVA hedges</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0610">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The reduced BA-CVA is also part of the full BA-CVA capital calculations as a conservative means to
restrict hedging efficiency, so all banks using the BA-CVA must make these calculations.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">make full BA-CVA capital calculations including the reduced BA-CVA</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:all banks using the BA-CVA">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">all banks using the BA-CVA</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0610">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">as a conservative means to restrict hedging efficiency</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0611">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Eligible single-name credit instruments must: (i) reference the counterparty directly;</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">reference the counterparty directly</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Eligible single-name credit instruments">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Eligible single-name credit instruments</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0612">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks that intend to use the full version of BA-CVA must calculate K reduced as well.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">calculate K reduced</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0612">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">intend to use the full version of BA-CVA</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0613">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Under the full
version, capital requirement for CVA risk K full is calculated as follows:
( )
K =β⋅K + 1−β ⋅K
full reduced hedged
where β=0.25 and is the supervisory parameter that is used to provide a floor that limits the extent to
which hedging can reduce the capital that is required to cover CVA risk.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">calculate capital requirement for CVA risk using the full formula incorporating a supervisory parameter beta</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:banks subject to CVA risk capital requirements">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">banks subject to CVA risk capital requirements</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0613">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when applying the full version of the capital requirement calculation for CVA risk</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0613">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">beta = 0.25</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0614">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The SA-CVA must be calculated and reported to supervisors at the same monthly frequency as
the SA-TB.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">calculate and report SA-CVA</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0614">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">at the same monthly frequency as SA-TB</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0614">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">monthly</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0615">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In addition, banks using the SA-CVA must calculate, and have the ability to produce to their
supervisors, SA-CVA calculations on demand.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">calculate, and have the ability to produce to their supervisors, SA-CVA calculations on demand</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:banks using the SA-CVA">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">banks using the SA-CVA</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0615">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">on demand</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0616">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Sensitivities must be computed by banks in
accordance with the sensitivity validation standards described for the SA-TB in the revised market risk
standard.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">compute sensitivities in accordance with the sensitivity validation standards described for the SA-TB</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0616">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">as specified in the revised market risk standard</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0617">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The minimum criteria for the SA-CVA eligibility include the following:
• A bank must be able to model exposure and calculate, on at least a monthly basis, CVA and CVA
sensitivities to the market risk factors specified in Section C.6 of this framework.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">be able to model exposure and calculate CVA and CVA sensitivities to the market risk factors specified in Section C.6 of this framework</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0617">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for SA-CVA eligibility</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0617">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">on at least a monthly basis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0618">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• A bank must have a CVA desk (or a similar dedicated function) responsible for risk management
and hedging of CVA.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have a CVA desk (or a similar dedicated function) responsible for risk management and hedging of CVA</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0619">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Calculations of regulatory CVA must be performed for each counterparty with which a bank has at
least one covered position.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">perform calculations of regulatory CVA</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0619">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">has at least one covered position with a counterparty</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0619">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">at least one covered position</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0620">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Regulatory CVA at a counterparty level must be calculated according to the following principles,
with the bank’s adherence to the principles to be demonstrated by the bank to its relevant supervisor:
• Regulatory CVA must be calculated as the expectation of future losses resulting from default of
the counterparty under the assumption that the bank itself is default risk-free.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">calculate Regulatory CVA as the expectation of future losses resulting from default of the counterparty under the assumption that the bank itself is default risk-free</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0620">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">at a counterparty level</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0621">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The calculation must be based on at least the following inputs: (i) term structure of market-
implied probability of default (PD);</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">The calculation must be based on at least the following inputs: (i) term structure of market-implied probability of default (PD)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0622">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The term structure of market-implied PD must be estimated from credit spreads observed in the
markets.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be estimated from credit spreads observed in the markets</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The term structure of market-implied PD">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The term structure of market-implied PD</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0623">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For counterparties whose credit is not actively traded (ie illiquid counterparties), the
market-implied PD must be estimated from proxy credit spreads estimated for these
counterparties according to the following requirements:
− A bank must estimate the credit spread curves of illiquid counterparties from credit spreads
observed in the markets of the counterparty’s liquid peers via an algorithm that discriminates
on at least three variables: a measure of credit quality (eg rating), industry, and region.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">estimate the credit spread curves of illiquid counterparties from credit spreads observed in the markets of the counterparty’s liquid peers via an algorithm that discriminates on at least three variables: a measure of credit quality (eg rating), industry, and region</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0623">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for counterparties whose credit is not actively traded (i.e. illiquid counterparties)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0623">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">at least three variables: a measure of credit quality, industry, and region</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0624">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A bank
must justify to its supervisor every case of mapping to single names.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must justify to its supervisor every case of mapping to single names</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0625">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">However,
where historical PDs are used as part of this assessment, the resulting spread cannot be
based on historical PD only – it must relate to credit markets.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure the resulting spread relates to credit markets and is not based on historical PD only</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the entity using historical PDs as part of the assessment">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the entity using historical PDs as part of the assessment</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0625">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where historical PDs are used as part of the assessment</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0626">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The market-consensus ELGD value used for regulatory CVA calculation must be the same as the
one used to calculate the risk-neutral PD from credit spreads unless the bank can demonstrate
that the seniority of the derivative exposure differs from the seniority of senior unsecured bonds.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use the same market-consensus ELGD value for regulatory CVA calculation as the one used to calculate the risk-neutral PD from credit spreads</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0626">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">unless the bank can demonstrate that the seniority of the derivative exposure differs from the seniority of senior unsecured bonds</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0626">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">if the bank can demonstrate that the seniority of the derivative exposure differs from the seniority of senior unsecured bonds</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0627">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• All market risk factors material for the transactions with a counterparty must be simulated as
stochastic processes for an appropriate number of paths defined on an appropriate set of future
time points extending to the maturity of the longest transaction.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be simulated as stochastic processes</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:All market risk factors material for the transactions with a counterparty">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">All market risk factors material for the transactions with a counterparty</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0627">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for an appropriate number of paths defined on an appropriate set of future time points extending to the maturity of the longest transaction</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0628">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">− All documentation used in collateralised transactions must be binding on all parties and
legally enforceable in all relevant jurisdictions.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">Ensure all documentation is binding and legally enforceable</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:All parties in collateralised transactions">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">All parties in collateralised transactions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0628">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">Documentation used in collateralised transactions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0629">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must have conducted sufficient legal
review to verify this and have a well-founded legal basis to reach this conclusion, and
undertake such further review as necessary to ensure continuing enforceability.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">conduct sufficient legal review to verify this and have a well-founded legal basis to reach this conclusion, and undertake such further review as necessary to ensure continuing enforceability</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0630">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• For margined counterparties, the exposure simulation must capture the effects of margining
collateral that is recognised as a risk mitigant along each exposure path.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">capture the effects of margining collateral that is recognised as a risk mitigant along each exposure path</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:margined counterparties">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">margined counterparties</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0630">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when conducting exposure simulation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0631">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">All the relevant
contractual features such as the nature of the margin agreement (unilateral vs bilateral), the
frequency of margin calls, the type of collateral, thresholds, independent amounts, initial margins
and minimum transfer amounts must be appropriately captured by the exposure model.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">appropriately capture all the relevant contractual features</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:exposure model">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">exposure model</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0631">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">such as the nature of the margin agreement (unilateral vs bilateral), the frequency of margin calls, the type of collateral, thresholds, independent amounts, initial margins and minimum transfer amounts</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0632">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">To
determine collateral available to a bank at a given exposure measurement time point, the
exposure model must assume that the counterparty will not post or return any collateral within a
certain time period immediately prior to that time point.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">assume that the counterparty will not post or return any collateral</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0632">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">within a certain time period immediately prior to the exposure measurement time point</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0633">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Model calibration process (with the exception of the MPoR), market and
transaction data used for regulatory CVA calculation must be the same as the ones used for accounting
CVA calculation.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be the same as the ones used for accounting CVA calculation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Model calibration process (with the exception of the MPoR), market and transaction data used for regulatory CVA calculation">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Model calibration process (with the exception of the MPoR), market and transaction data used for regulatory CVA calculation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0633">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">Model calibration process with the exception of the MPoR</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0634">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The generation of market risk factor paths underlying the exposure models must satisfy the
following requirements, with the bank’s adherence to these requirements to be demonstrated by the bank
to its relevant supervisor:
• Drifts of risk factors must be consistent with a risk-neutral probability measure.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure drifts of risk factors are consistent with a risk-neutral probability measure</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0634">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in the generation of market risk factor paths underlying the exposure models</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0635">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The volatilities and correlations of market risk factors must be calibrated to market data whenever
sufficient data exists in a given market.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be calibrated to market data</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The volatilities and correlations of market risk factors">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The volatilities and correlations of market risk factors</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0635">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">whenever sufficient data exists in a given market</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0636">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The distribution of modelled risk factors must account for the possible non-normality of the
distribution of exposures, including the existence of leptokurtosis (“fat tails”), where appropriate.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must account for the possible non-normality of the distribution of exposures, including the existence of leptokurtosis ("fat tails")</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The distribution of modelled risk factors">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The distribution of modelled risk factors</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0636">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">where appropriate</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0637">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In particular, all components of accounting-
based exposure models must be independently validated.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be independently validated</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:all components of accounting-based exposure models">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">all components of accounting-based exposure models</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0637">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">in particular</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0638">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The following requirements apply, with the bank’s adherence to these requirements to be
demonstrated by the bank to its relevant supervisor:
• Exposure models used for calculating regulatory CVA must be part of a CVA risk management
framework that includes the identification, measurement, management, approval and internal
116 Basel III: Finalising post-crisis reforms
reporting of CVA market risk.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use exposure models that are part of a CVA risk management framework including identification, measurement, management, approval and internal reporting of CVA market risk for calculating regulatory CVA</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0638">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when using exposure models for calculating regulatory CVA</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0639">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">A bank must have a credible track record in using these exposure
models for calculating CVA and CVA sensitivities to market risk factors.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have a credible track record in using these exposure models for calculating CVA and CVA sensitivities to market risk factors</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0640">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• Senior management should be actively involved in the risk control process and must regard CVA
risk control as an essential aspect of the business to which significant resources need to be
devoted.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">be actively involved in the risk control process and regard CVA risk control as an essential aspect of the business to which significant resources need to be devoted</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0641">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• Banks must have a process in place for ensuring compliance with a documented set of internal
policies, controls and procedures concerning the operation of the exposure system used for
accounting CVA calculations.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have a process in place for ensuring compliance with a documented set of internal policies, controls and procedures concerning the operation of the exposure system used for accounting CVA calculations</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0642">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• Banks must have an independent control unit that is responsible for the effective initial and
ongoing validation of the exposure models.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have an independent control unit responsible for the effective initial and ongoing validation of the exposure models</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0643">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">This unit must be independent from business credit
and trading units (including the CVA desk), must be adequately staffed and must report directly
to senior management of the firm.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be independent from business credit and trading units (including the CVA desk), must be adequately staffed, and must report directly to senior management of the firm</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:This unit">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">This unit</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0644">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• Banks must document the process for initial and ongoing validation of their exposure models to
a level of detail that would enable a third party to understand how the model operates, its
limitations, and its key assumptions;</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">document the process for initial and ongoing validation of their exposure models to a level of detail that would enable a third party to understand how the model operates, its limitations, and its key assumptions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0645">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">This documentation must set out
the minimum frequency with which ongoing validation will be conducted as well as other
circumstances (such as a sudden change in market behaviour).</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">set out the minimum frequency with which ongoing validation will be conducted as well as other circumstances</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:This documentation">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">This documentation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0645">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">such as a sudden change in market behaviour</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0646">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In addition, the documentation
must describe how the validation is conducted with respect to data flows and portfolios, what
analyses are used and how representative counterparty portfolios are constructed.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">describe how the validation is conducted with respect to data flows and portfolios, what analyses are used and how representative counterparty portfolios are constructed</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:the documentation">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">the documentation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0647">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The pricing models used to calculate exposure for a given path of market risk factors must be
tested against appropriate independent benchmarks for a wide range of market states as part of
the initial and ongoing model validation process.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be tested against appropriate independent benchmarks for a wide range of market states</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The pricing models used to calculate exposure for a given path of market risk factors">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The pricing models used to calculate exposure for a given path of market risk factors</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0647">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">as part of the initial and ongoing model validation process</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0648">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Pricing models for options must account for
the non-linearity of option value with respect to market risk factors.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">account for the non-linearity of option value with respect to market risk factors</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Pricing models for options">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Pricing models for options</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0649">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• Banks must define criteria on which to assess the exposure models and their inputs and have a
written policy in place to describe the process by which unacceptable performance will be
determined and remedied.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">define criteria to assess exposure models and their inputs and have a written policy describing the process to determine and remedy unacceptable performance</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0650">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• An exposure model must capture transaction-specific information in order to aggregate
exposures at the level of the netting set.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">capture transaction-specific information in order to aggregate exposures at the level of the neting set</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:An exposure model">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">An exposure model</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0651">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must verify that transactions are assigned to the
appropriate netting set within the model.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">verify that transactions are assigned to the appropriate netting set within the model</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0652">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The exposure models must reflect transaction terms and specifications in a timely, complete, and
conservative fashion.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">reflect transaction terms and specifications in a timely, complete, and conservative fashion</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The exposure models">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The exposure models</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0653">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The terms and specifications must reside in a secure database that is subject
to formal and periodic audit.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">reside in a secure database</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The terms and specifications">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The terms and specifications</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0653">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">that is subject to formal and periodic audit</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0654">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The transmission of transaction terms and specifications data to the
exposure model must also be subject to internal audit, and formal reconciliation processes must
be in place between the internal model and source data systems to verify on an ongoing basis
that transaction terms and specifications are being reflected in the exposure system correctly or
at least conservatively.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">Subject the transmission of transaction terms and specifications data to internal audit and maintain formal reconciliation processes between the internal model and source data systems</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The entity transmitting transaction terms and specifications data">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The entity transmitting transaction terms and specifications data</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0654">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">To verify on an ongoing basis that transaction terms and specifications are being reflected in the exposure system correctly or at least conservatively</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0654">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">on an ongoing basis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0655">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• The current and historical market data must be acquired independently of the lines of business
and be compliant with accounting.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">acquire current and historical market data independently of the lines of business and ensure compliance with accounting standards</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The entity responsible for acquiring market data">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The entity responsible for acquiring market data</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0656">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">They must be fed into the exposure model in a timely and
complete fashion, and maintained in a secure database subject to formal and periodic audit.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">be fed into the exposure model in a timely and complete fashion, and maintained in a secure database</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0656">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">subject to formal and periodic audit</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0657">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must also have a well-developed data integrity process to handle the data of erroneous
and/or anomalous observations.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have a well-developed data integrity process to handle the data of erroneous and/or anomalous observations</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0658">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">To the extent that the exposure model relies on proxy market
data, internal policies must identify suitable proxies and the bank must demonstrate empirically
on an ongoing basis that the proxy provides a conservative representation of the underlying risk
under adverse market conditions.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">demonstrate empirically on an ongoing basis that the proxy provides a conservative representation of the underlying risk under adverse market conditions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0658">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to the extent that the exposure model relies on proxy market data</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0658">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">on an ongoing basis</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0659">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">If an instrument is deemed as an eligible hedge for credit spread delta risk, it must be assigned
in its entirety (see footnote 7) either to the counterparty credit spread or to the reference credit spread
risk type.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be assigned in its entirety either to the counterparty credit spread or to the reference credit spread risk type</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:an instrument">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">an instrument</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0659">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if an instrument is deemed as an eligible hedge for credit spread delta risk</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0659">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">see footnote 7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0660">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">When CVA sensitivities for vega risk are calculated, the volatility shift must apply to both types of
volatilities that appear in exposure models: (i) volatilities used for generating risk factor paths;</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">apply volatility shift to both types of volatilities used in exposure models</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:CVA sensitivities calculation process">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">CVA sensitivities calculation process</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0660">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when CVA sensitivities for vega risk are calculated</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0661">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">CVA sensitivities for vega risk are always material and must be
calculated regardless of whether or not the portfolio includes options.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be calculated</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:CVA sensitivities for vega risk">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">CVA sensitivities for vega risk</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0661">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">regardless of whether or not the portfolio includes options</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0662">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">If a hedging instrument is an index, its sensitivities to all risk factors upon which the value of the
index depends must be calculated.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">calculate sensitivities to all risk factors upon which the value of the index depends</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:hedging instrument">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">hedging instrument</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0662">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if the hedging instrument is an index</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0663">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The index sensitivity to risk factor k must be calculated via applying the
shift of risk factor k to all index constituents that depend on this risk factor and recalculating the index.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be calculated via applying the shift of risk factor k to all index constituents that depend on this risk factor and recalculating the index</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The index">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The index</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0663">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when assessing sensitivity to risk factor k</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0664">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For example, to calculate delta sensitivity of S&amp;P500 to large financial companies, banks must apply the
relevant shift to equity prices of all large financial companies that are constituents of S&amp;P500 and re-
compute the index.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">apply the relevant shift to equity prices of all large financial companies that are constituents of S&amp;P500 and re-compute the index</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0664">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to calculate delta sensitivity of S&amp;P500 to large financial companies</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0665">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Weighted sensitivities must be aggregated into a capital charge K b within each bucket b (the
buckets and correlation parameters ρ applicable to each risk type are specified in Section C.6).</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">Aggregate weighted sensitivities into a capital charge K_b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Financial institution">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Financial institution</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0665">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">Within each bucket b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0666">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Bucket-level capital charges must then be aggregated across buckets within each risk type (the
correlation parameters γ applicable to each risk type are specified in Section C.6.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">Aggregate bucket-level capital charges across buckets within each risk type</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Banks or financial institutions subject to capital requirements">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Banks or financial institutions subject to capital requirements</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0666">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">When calculating capital requirements for each risk type</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0667">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• To assign a risk exposure to a sector, banks must rely on a classification that is commonly used
in the market for grouping issuers by industry sector.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">assign a risk exposure to a sector using a classification commonly used in the market for grouping issuers by industry sector</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0667">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when assigning a risk exposure to a sector</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0668">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The bank must assign each issuer to one of
the sector buckets in the table above and it must assign all issuers from the same industry to the
same sector.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">assign each issuer to one of the sector buckets in the table above and assign all issuers from the same industry to the same sector</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0668">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if the issuer is from the same industry</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0669">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Risk positions from any issuer that a bank cannot assign to a sector in this fashion
must be assigned to the “other sector” (ie bucket 11).</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">assign risk positions from any issuer that cannot be assigned to a sector to the 'other sector' (bucket 11)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0669">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">if a bank cannot assign risk positions from an issuer to a sector</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0670">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">For multinational multi-sector equity
issuers, the allocation to a particular bucket must be done according to the most material region
and sector in which the issuer operates.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">allocate to a particular bucket according to the most material region and sector in which the issuer operates</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:multinational multi-sector equity issuers">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">multinational multi-sector equity issuers</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0670">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when allocating to a particular bucket</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0671">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">That is, a bank with losses that
are high relative to its BIC is required to hold higher capital due to the incorporation of internal losses into
the calculation methodology.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">hold higher capital</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:a bank with losses that are high relative to its BIC">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">a bank with losses that are high relative to its BIC</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0671">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">due to the incorporation of internal losses into the calculation methodology</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0672">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">That
is, a bank with losses that are low relative to its BIC is required to hold lower capital due to the
incorporation of internal losses into the calculation methodology.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">hold lower capital</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:a bank with losses that are low relative to its BIC">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">a bank with losses that are low relative to its BIC</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0672">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">due to the incorporation of internal losses into the calculation methodology</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0673">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The calculation of average losses in the Loss Component must be based on 10 years of high-
quality annual loss data.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">calculate average losses based on 10 years of high-quality annual loss data</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The entity calculating the Loss Component">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The entity calculating the Loss Component</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0673">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">during the calculation of the Loss Component</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0673">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">10 years</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0674">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">As part of the transition to the standardised approach, banks that do not have 10 years of high-
quality loss data may use a minimum of five years of data to calculate the Loss Component.4 Banks that
do not have five years of high-quality loss data must calculate the capital requirement based solely on the
BI Component.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use a minimum of five years of data to calculate the Loss Component</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:banks that do not have 10 years of high-quality loss data">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">banks that do not have 10 years of high-quality loss data</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0674">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">as part of the transition to the standardised approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0674">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">10 years of high-quality loss data</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0675">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Similar to bank holding companies, when BI figures for sub-consolidated or subsidiary banks
reach bucket 2, these banks are required to use loss experience in the standardised approach calculations.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use loss experience in the standardised approach calculations</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:sub-consolidated or subsidiary banks">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">sub-consolidated or subsidiary banks</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0675">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when BI figures reach bucket 2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0676">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In case a subsidiary of a bank belonging to bucket 2 or higher does not meet the qualitative
standards for the use of the Loss Component, this subsidiary must calculate the standardised approach
capital requirements by applying 100% of the BI Component.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">calculate the standardised approach capital requirements by applying 100% of the BI Component</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:a subsidiary of a bank belonging to bucket 2 or higher">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">a subsidiary of a bank belonging to bucket 2 or higher</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0676">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">does not meet the qualitative standards for the use of the Loss Component</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0676">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">100%</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0677">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks with a BI greater than €1bn are required to use loss data as a direct input into the
operational risk capital calculations.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use loss data as a direct input into the operational risk capital calculations</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Banks with a BI greater than €1bn">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Banks with a BI greater than €1bn</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0677">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">BI greater than €1bn</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0677">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">€1bn</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0678">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks which do not meet the loss data standards are required to hold capital that is at a minimum
equal to 100% of the BIC.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">hold capital that is at a minimum equal to 100% of the BIC</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0678">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">which do not meet the loss data standards</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0678">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">100%</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0679">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The exclusion of internal loss data due to non-compliance with the loss data standards, and the
application of any resulting multipliers, must be publicly disclosed.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">publicly disclose the exclusion of internal loss data due to non-compliance with the loss data standards and the application of any resulting multipliers</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The entity excluding internal loss data">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The entity excluding internal loss data</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0679">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when internal loss data is excluded due to non-compliance with the loss data standards</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0680">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">130 Basel III: Finalising post-crisis reforms
(a) Internally generated loss data calculations used for regulatory capital purposes must be based
on a 10-year observation period.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be based on a 10-year observation period</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Internally generated loss data calculations used for regulatory capital purposes">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Internally generated loss data calculations used for regulatory capital purposes</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0680">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">10-year</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0681">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Therefore, a bank must have
documented procedures and processes for the identification, collection and treatment of internal
loss data.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have documented procedures and processes for the identification, collection and treatment of internal loss data</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0682">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Such procedures and processes must be subject to validation before the use of the loss
data within the operational risk capital requirement measurement methodology, and to regular
independent reviews by internal and/or external audit functions.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be subject to validation before the use of the loss data within the operational risk capital requirement measurement methodology, and to regular independent reviews by internal and/or external audit functions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Such procedures and processes">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Such procedures and processes</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0682">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">before the use of the loss data within the operational risk capital requirement measurement methodology</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0682">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">before the use of the loss data</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0683">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The bank must document criteria for allocating losses to the specified event types.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">document criteria for allocating losses to the specified event types</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0683">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">specified event types</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0684">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">(d) A bank’s internal loss data must be comprehensive and capture all material activities and
exposures from all appropriate subsystems and geographic locations.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must maintain internal loss data that is comprehensive and captures all material activities and exposures from all appropriate subsystems and geographic locations</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0685">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">(e) Aside from information on gross loss amounts, the bank must collect information about the
reference dates of operational risk events, including the date when the event happened or first
began (“date of occurrence”), where available;</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">collect information about the reference dates of operational risk events, including the date when the event happened or first began</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0685">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">aside from information on gross loss amounts</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0685">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">where available</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0686">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In addition, the bank must collect information on recoveries of gross loss amounts
as well as descriptive information about the drivers or causes of the loss event.6 The level of detail
of any descriptive information should be commensurate with the size of the gross loss amount.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">collect information on recoveries of gross loss amounts as well as descriptive information about the drivers or causes of the loss event</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0686">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">the level of detail of any descriptive information should be commensurate with the size of the gross loss amount</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0687">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">(h) Banks must have processes to independently review the comprehensiveness and accuracy of loss
data.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">have processes to independently review the comprehensiveness and accuracy of loss data</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0688">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must be able to identify the gross loss amounts, non-insurance recoveries, and insurance
recoveries for all operational loss events.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">identify the gross loss amounts, non-insurance recoveries, and insurance recoveries for all operational loss events</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0688">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for all operational loss events</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0689">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Verification of payments received to net losses
must be provided to supervisors upon request.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">provide verification of payments received to net losses</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0689">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">upon request by supervisors</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0690">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The following items must be included in the gross loss computation of the loss data set:
(a) Direct charges, including impairments and settlements, to the bank’s P&amp;L accounts and write-
downs due to the operational risk event;</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">include direct charges, including impairments and settlements, to the bank’s P&amp;L accounts and write-downs due to the operational risk event in the gross loss computation of the loss data set</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0690">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">due to the operational risk event</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0691">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must use the date of accounting for building the loss data set.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use the date of accounting for building the loss data set</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0692">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The bank must use a date
no later than the date of accounting for including losses related to legal events in the loss data set.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use a date no later than the date of accounting for including losses related to legal events in the loss data set</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0692">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when including losses related to legal events in the loss data set</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0692">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">no later than the date of accounting</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0693">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The total loss amount and number of exclusions must be disclosed under Pillar 3 with appropriate
narratives, including total loss amount and number of exclusions.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">disclose the total loss amount and number of exclusions with appropriate narratives</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Financial institutions subject to Pillar 3 disclosure requirements">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Financial institutions subject to Pillar 3 disclosure requirements</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0693">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">under Pillar 3 disclosure framework</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0694">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Such exclusions must be disclosed under Pillar 3.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be disclosed</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Such exclusions">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Such exclusions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0694">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">under Pillar 3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0695">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Losses and the measurement of the BI must include losses and BI items that result from
acquisitions of relevant business and mergers.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">include losses and BI items that result from acquisitions of relevant business and mergers</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Losses and the measurement of the BI">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Losses and the measurement of the BI</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0695">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when there are acquisitions of relevant business and mergers</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0696">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">All banks with a BI greater than €1bn, or which use internal loss data in the calculation of
operational risk capital, are required to disclose their annual loss data for each of the ten years in the ILM
calculation window.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">disclose their annual loss data for each of the ten years in the ILM calculation window</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:All banks with a BI greater than €1bn, or which use internal loss data in the calculation of operational risk capital">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">All banks with a BI greater than €1bn, or which use internal loss data in the calculation of operational risk capital</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0696">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">BI greater than €1bn or use of internal loss data in the calculation of operational risk capital</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0696">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">€1bn</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0696">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">annual</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0697">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Loss data
is required to be reported on both a gross basis and after recoveries and loss exclusions.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">report loss data on both a gross basis and after recoveries and loss exclusions</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0698">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The output floor will ensure that banks’ capital requirements do not fall below a certain percentage of
capital requirements derived under standardised approaches.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">ensure that banks’ capital requirements do not fall below a certain percentage of capital requirements derived under standardised approaches</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The output floor">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The output floor</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0698">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">a certain percentage</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0699">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">As set out in the Basel III framework, banks must meet the following capital requirements:
• Common Equity Tier 1 must be at least 4.5% of risk-weighted assets at all times.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">meet Common Equity Tier 1 capital requirement of at least 4.5% of risk-weighted assets</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0699">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">at all times</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0699">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">4.5%</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0700">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• Tier 1 capital must be at least 6.0% of risk-weighted assets at all times.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">must be at least 6.0% of risk-weighted assets</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:Tier 1 capital">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">Tier 1 capital</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0700">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">at all times</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0700">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">6.0%</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0701">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• Total Capital (Tier 1 capital and Tier 2 capital) must be at least 8.0% of risk-weighted assets at all
times.1
3.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">Maintain total capital (Tier 1 capital and Tier 2 capital) at least 8.0% of risk-weighted assets</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0701">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">At all times</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0701">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">8.0%</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0702">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The risk-weighted assets that banks must use to determine compliance with the requirements set
out in paragraphs 2 to 3 above must be calculated as the maximum of: (i) the total risk-weighted assets
calculated using the approaches that the bank has supervisory approval to use in accordance with the
Basel capital framework (including both standardised and internally-modelled based approaches);</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">calculate risk-weighted assets as the maximum of the total risk-weighted assets calculated using the approaches that the bank has supervisory approval to use in accordance with the Basel capital framework</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0702">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to determine compliance with the requirements set out in paragraphs 2 to 3 above</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0703">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The standardised approaches to be used when calculating the output floor described in
paragraph 4 are as follows:
• Credit risk: the standardised approach for credit risk.4 When calculating the degree of credit risk
mitigation, banks must use the carrying value when applying the simple approach or the
1 The Basel III framework is available at www.bis.org/publ/bcbs189.pdf.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use the carrying value when applying the simple approach</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0703">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when calculating the degree of credit risk mitigation</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0704">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• Counterparty credit risk: to calculate the exposure for derivatives, banks must use the
standardised approach for measuring counterparty credit risk (SA-CCR).</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use the standardised approach for measuring counterparty credit risk (SA-CCR)</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0704">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to calculate the exposure for derivatives</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0705">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The exposure amounts
must then be multiplied by the relevant borrower risk weight using the standardised approach
for credit risk to calculate RWA under the standardised approach for credit risk.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">multiply exposure amounts by the relevant borrower risk weight using the standardised approach for credit risk to calculate RWA</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0705">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to calculate RWA under the standardised approach for credit risk</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0706">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The SEC-ERBA, SEC-SA or a risk-weight of
1250% must also be used when determining the default risk charge component for securitisations
held in the trading book.7
• Operational risk: the standardised approach for operational risk.8
7.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">use a risk-weight of 1250% when determining the default risk charge component for securitisations held in the trading book</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:SEC-ERBA, SEC-SA">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">SEC-ERBA, SEC-SA</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0706">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">when determining the default risk charge component for securitisations held in the trading book</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0706">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">1250%</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0707">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The table below provides a simple example of how the capital floor must be calculated.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">calculate the capital floor</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0707">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">as shown in the table</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0708">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must disclose two sets of risk-weighted capital ratios: (i) ratios that exclude the capital floor
in the calculation of risk-weighted assets;</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">disclose two sets of risk-weighted capital ratios</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0708">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">ratios that exclude the capital floor in the calculation of risk-weighted assets</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0709">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In addition, banks must disclose more granular information related to the calculation
of their risk-weighted assets under internally-modelled and standardised approaches, which will be set
out in forthcoming disclosure templates as part of the Committee’s Pillar 3 disclosure framework.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">disclose more granular information related to the calculation of their risk-weighted assets under internally-modelled and standardised approaches</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0709">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">as part of the Committee’s Pillar 3 disclosure framework</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DEAD:OBL-0709">
      <data key="d2">deadline</data>
      <data key="d6">when the forthcoming disclosure templates are issued</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0710">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must meet a 3% leverage ratio minimum requirement at all times.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">meet a 3% leverage ratio minimum requirement</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0710">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">at all times</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0710">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">3%</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0711">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">In addition, to maintain the relative roles of the risk-weighted and leverage ratio requirements,
banks identified as global systemically-important banks (G-SIBs) according the G-SIB standard must also
meet a leverage ratio buffer requirement.2 Consistent with the capital measure required to meet the
1 Basel Committee on Banking Supervision, Basel III: A global regulatory framework for more resilient banks and banking systems,
June 2011, www.bis.org/publ/bcbs189.pdf.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">meet a leverage ratio buffer requirement</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:banks identified as global systemically-important banks (G-SIBs) according to the G-SIB standard">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">banks identified as global systemically-important banks (G-SIBs) according to the G-SIB standard</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0711">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">to maintain the relative roles of the risk-weighted and leverage ratio requirements</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0712">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">140 Basel III: Finalising post-crisis reforms
leverage ratio minimum described in paragraph 5, G-SIBs must meet the leverage ratio buffer with Tier 1
capital.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">meet the leverage ratio buffer with Tier 1 capital</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:G-SIBs">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">G-SIBs</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0712">
      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">as described in paragraph 5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THRE:OBL-0712">
      <data key="d2">threshold</data>
      <data key="d6">leverage ratio minimum</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0713">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">The leverage ratio buffer requirement on 1 January 2022 shall be based on the Financial Stability
Board’s 2020 list of G-SIBs (based on end-2019 data).</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">shall be based on the Financial Stability Board’s 2020 list of G-SIBs</data>
    </node>
    <node id="SUBJ:The leverage ratio buffer requirement">
      <data key="d2">subject</data>
      <data key="d6">The leverage ratio buffer requirement</data>
