      <data key="d2">condition</data>
      <data key="d6">for the purpose of the leverage ratio exposure measure</data>
    </node>
    <node id="EXCE:OBL-0722">
      <data key="d2">exception</data>
      <data key="d6">may offset between those cash receivables and cash payables if the financial assets bought and sold that are associated with cash payables and receivables are fair valued through income and included in the bank’s regulatory trading book as specified by paragraphs 8 to 20 of the market risk framework</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OBL-0723">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">• the bank (i) has a legally enforceable right to transfer the balances of the individual participating
customer accounts into a single account so that the bank is not liable for the balances on an
individual basis and (ii) at any point in time, the bank must have the discretion and be in a position
to exercise this right;</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">has a legally enforceable right to transfer the balances of the individual participating customer accounts into a single account and must have the discretion and be in a position to exercise this right at any point in time</data>
    </node>
    <node id="COND:OBL-0723">
