    <node id="OBL-0725">
      <data key="d2">obligation</data>
      <data key="d3">Banks must calculate their exposures associated with all derivative transactions, including where
a bank sells protection using a credit derivative, as a scalar multiplier alpha set at 1.4 times the sum of the
RC14 and the PFE, as described in paragraph 34.</data>
      <data key="d4">Section XI</data>
      <data key="d5">calculate their exposures associated with all derivative transactions, including where a bank sells protection using a credit derivative, as a scalar multiplier alpha set at 1.4 times the sum of the RC14 and the PFE</data>
    </node>
